Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.25,0:00:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of the Governing Body\Nand all of those working
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.26,0:00:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.34,0:00:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s my pleasure to welcome you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to the 2022 “Pursue Peace”! Convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These convention segments,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.02,0:00:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which constitute special editions
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.44,0:00:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting® this month and next,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,have been translated\Ninto more than 500 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.86,0:00:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture theme\Nfor this session and the next
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.28,0:00:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is Psalm 29:11:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.45,0:01:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah will bless his people with peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch\Nthe following music-video presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.92,0:01:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the peace we find
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.67,0:01:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by observing Jehovah’s creations,\Nreading his Word,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.18,0:01:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and sharing his message with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.06,0:01:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.58,0:10:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We are delighted you could join us\Nfor the opening session
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.92,0:10:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of the “Pursue Peace”! Convention\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s sing together song number 86, entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.05,0:10:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“We Must Be Taught.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s song number 86.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:13:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of peace does God give,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.09,0:13:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and to whom does he give it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.72,0:13:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Stephen Lett, a member\Nof the Governing Body of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will answer these questions\Nin the opening talk of our program.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.65,0:13:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention\Nas he develops the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah Is ‘the God Who Gives Peace.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my great pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to warmly welcome all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and to say, {\i1}{s16}{nArial}“Shalom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is saying that appropriate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, {\i1}{s16}{nArial}shalom {
} is the Hebrew word for “peace,”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it occurs over 200 times in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When it’s used as a greeting\N(just as I used it),
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.81,0:13:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it means: “May you have peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.90,0:13:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what could be a more appropriate way\Nto greet all of you at the start
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of this “Pursue Peace”!\NConvention of Jehovah’s Witnesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.91,0:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very pleased that you’re with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and we assure you\Nthat you will not be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.66,0:14:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To the contrary, you’ll be glad you were able
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.71,0:14:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to devote three days to learning\Nwhat the Bible says
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to gain and maintain peace
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.55,0:14:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in all areas of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s begin\Nby talking about the Person
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.85,0:14:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,who has drawn us all together\Nfor this convention—Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.02,0:14:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And how we delight in talking
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about our marvelous heavenly Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians 4:9
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,calls Jehovah “the God of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s true\Nthat he possesses many qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—love, justice, wisdom, power—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.12,0:14:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also possesses the quality of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.45,0:14:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about it,\Nhe is at peace with himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at peace with angels,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:14:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at peace with faithful humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he is “the God of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s a question:\NDoes Jehovah keep this peace to himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s get the answer\Nat Romans chapter 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.26,0:15:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans chapter 15
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and please let’s read verse 33:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“May the God who gives peace
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.44,0:15:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,be with all of you. Amen.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So he generously gives this peace,\Nas we’ll be discussing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he gives\N“every good gift and every perfect present,”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,according to James 1:17.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.58,0:15:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of his finest presents\Nis the gift of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s another question:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.38,0:15:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of peace does Jehovah give?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, many equate peace
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.72,0:15:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with freedom from conflict\Nand strife in one’s life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.55,0:15:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the peace Jehovah gives\Nis a lot more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.22,0:15:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The peace that only Jehovah can supply
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:15:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,brings in feelings of safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.77,0:16:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,security, well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This Jehovah-given peace
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is described very nicely\Nin Philippians chapter 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.95,0:16:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians chapter 4 beginning in verse 6:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious over anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in everything by prayer and supplication
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.96,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“along with thanksgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“let your petitions be made known to God;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.63,0:16:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the peace of God\Nthat surpasses all understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“will guard your hearts\Nand your mental powers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of Christ Jesus.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So notice that Jehovah is saying:\N“Do not be anxious over anything.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.23,0:16:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jehovah tell us to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that was impossible for us to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.07,0:16:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But, obviously, he’s talking about not being
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.74,0:16:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,overly anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.37,0:16:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Controlled anxiety\Ncan actually be beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It can move us to show concern for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It can motivate us to work enthusiastically\Nto accomplish an assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what about excessive,\Nuncontrolled anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that can lead to physical problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression can be crippling,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,debilitating, enfeebling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.64,0:17:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, how can we avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.97,0:17:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,being overly anxious over anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.23,0:17:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is given in the next words\Nof Philippians 4:6, 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.86,0:17:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,After telling us not to be anxious,\NJehovah gives the antidote.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.49,0:17:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He basically tells us to pray,\Nsupplicate, and petition him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.16,0:17:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will get that “peace of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what does the scripture mean
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when it says that this ‘peace of God
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,surpasses all understanding’?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we could say\Nthat it’s so amazing and so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that we limited humans\Ncannot fully understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:18:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It defies logic from a human standpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hearts and minds may be filled\Nwith so much worry, fear, anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.69,0:18:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see no way out, but we beg Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the peace that he can supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.28,0:18:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Our minds and hearts\Nare amazingly filled with calmness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,security, tranquility.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Loraine, a young girl
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,whose mother was dying\Nof cancer, said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was in the room\Nwhen my mother took her last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.59,0:18:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“I . . . asked Jehovah\Nto give me the strength
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.72,0:18:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“to endure and to get through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.80,0:18:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I immediately felt the peace of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what is meant by the expression
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.65,0:18:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“the peace of God . . .\Nwill guard your hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and your mental powers”?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.65,0:18:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Greek word translated “guard”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.20,0:18:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is a military term\Nthat evokes a mental picture
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:19:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of soldiers\Nmaintaining a day-and-night watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.16,0:19:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,this peace of God\Ncan act like a 24-hour guard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.67,0:19:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,over our hearts and mental powers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.84,0:19:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—keeping them calm, secure, and tranquil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.30,0:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the key ingredient
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.68,0:19:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to our being able to receive\Nthis miraculous peace of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer:\NHaving a close friendship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.94,0:19:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul\Nexperienced firsthand many times
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.82,0:19:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that having inner peace depends,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not on circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather, on a close,\Npersonal relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, on one occasion
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because Paul and Silas boldly preached,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.37,0:19:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they had their garments ripped off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.46,0:19:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They were beaten—many blows with rods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They were thrown into the inner prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Their feet were fastened in stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.01,0:20:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.10,0:20:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what did Paul and Silas begin to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.93,0:20:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They began to pray\Nand sing songs of praise to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In amazement,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.27,0:20:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all the other prisoners\Nwere listening to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.78,0:20:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously, their very,\Nvery unfavorable circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.49,0:20:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,had not robbed them\Nof their precious peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.41,0:20:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s learn\Nthis valuable lesson from Paul and Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.00,0:20:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Having the peace of God
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is not dependent on our circumstances,\Nbut it is dependent
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.84,0:20:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,on having a close,\Npersonal relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus far, we’ve discussed how Jehovah\Nis the God of peace who gives peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ve talked\Nabout what kind of peace he gives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.81,0:20:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.68,0:20:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom does Jehovah give peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The simple answer is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gives peace\Nto those who draw close to him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to follow his guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So receiving peace from Jehovah starts
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with living a clean life,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.37,0:21:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,following Jehovah’s\Nrighteous moral standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.50,0:21:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people in Satan’s world, as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,believe that God will accept them as they are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—that God in effect\Nwill lower his standard to accommodate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.51,0:21:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine such pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.89,0:21:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be like a pot\Ntelling its maker, the potter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how the pot must be used,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.35,0:21:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the potter must accept this,\Nwhether he likes it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.27,0:21:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know\Nit doesn’t work that way, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.82,0:21:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to come up\Nto Jehovah’s righteous standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.95,0:21:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he’ll help us, but we do the changing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,—certainly not Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.49,0:21:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly, James 3:17
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,says that “the wisdom from above
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.13,0:21:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“is first of all pure,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:21:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,then peaceable.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.55,0:22:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we want peace from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that will result in peaceful lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.89,0:22:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we must be pure\Naccording to Jehovah’s moral standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.56,0:22:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 48:22 reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.31,0:22:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘There is no peace,’\Nsays Jehovah, ‘for the wicked.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.11,0:22:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or put another way,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.90,0:22:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,those who wickedly set\Ntheir own moral standards
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.74,0:22:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will receive no peace from Jehovah\Nand will not have peaceful lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.74,0:22:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But we work hard\Nto live by Jehovah’s standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.45,0:22:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s true\Nthat Jehovah does his part to help us,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.29,0:22:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but he does expect us to do our part.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.17,0:22:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say that his blessing on our effort
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.21,0:22:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is somewhat like multiplication.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.05,0:22:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we put forth no effort,\Nthere’s nothing for Jehovah to multiply.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.47,0:22:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is ten times zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.60,0:22:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.06,0:22:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a hundred times zero?\Na thousand times zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.44,0:22:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a million times zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.23,0:22:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.90,0:23:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we don’t do anything,\NJehovah has nothing to multiply.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 5:22 tells us that peace
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.07,0:23:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is an aspect\Nof “the fruitage of the [holy] spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.83,0:23:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the holy spirit will help us\Ncultivate and demonstrate peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.54,0:23:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, John 14:26
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.17,0:23:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the holy spirit as a “helper.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.88,0:23:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But that expression “helper”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.01,0:23:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t indicate\Nit will miraculously do the job for us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.05,0:23:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with no effort on our part.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.47,0:23:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate this if we can:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.47,0:23:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that you’re working very hard
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.31,0:23:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to paint the outside of your house,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.98,0:23:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good friend comes to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you’re painting together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.15,0:23:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But then you decide,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.07,0:23:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll just go back in the house,\Nand I’ll just take it easy.’
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.03,0:23:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how long\Nwill your friend keep painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If he continued painting,\Nhe’s no longer a helper;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.25,0:23:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s doing the job for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.58,0:24:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 11:13 tells us that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.79,0:24:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,will “give holy spirit\Nto those asking him” for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.17,0:24:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we ask for holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.51,0:24:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then do our very best\Nto work in harmony with that helper,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.60,0:24:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we will enjoy peace with God
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will enjoy and promote harmony,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.27,0:24:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,unity, and good relations with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.81,0:24:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a pleasure it is\Nto associate with those who display peace
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—this important aspect\Nof the spirit’s fruitage!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.03,0:24:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When a sleeping baby
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.16,0:24:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is suddenly awakened\Nin the middle of the night by a loud noise,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.17,0:24:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he becomes frightened\N—doesn’t he?—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.38,0:24:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he cries out for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.71,0:24:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But when a parent cuddles him
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.59,0:24:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and soothes him with reassuring words,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.38,0:24:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he calms down immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.76,0:24:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, David at Psalm 55:16-18
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.77,0:25:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,said that when he was troubled,\Nhe ‘called out to God’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.48,0:25:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Jehovah\N‘heard his voice’ and ‘gave him peace.’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.49,0:25:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Like David, when we’re in anguish,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.86,0:25:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we can supplicate our heavenly Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.99,0:25:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will soothe and restore our peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.00,0:25:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, our loving Father\Nis eager to do this for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.00,0:25:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up to Jeremiah chapter 29,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.46,0:25:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice that he’s eager\Nto replace our anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.09,0:25:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with the peace from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.93,0:25:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 29:11:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.43,0:25:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I well know the thoughts\Nthat I am thinking toward you,’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.35,0:25:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.65,0:25:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘thoughts of peace, and not of calamity,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.19,0:25:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘to give you a future and a hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.86,0:25:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And you will call me\Nand come and pray to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.87,0:25:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will listen to you.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.16,0:26:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.04,0:26:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Our God is ready, willing, and able\Nto replace our anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.04,0:26:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with this amazing peace\Nthat only he can give.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.92,0:26:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ve now discussed\Nhow Jehovah is the God of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.22,0:26:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve discussed who he gives the peace to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.10,0:26:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—to those who draw close to him
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.56,0:26:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and earnestly seek peace from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.56,0:26:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s examine how each of us
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.52,0:26:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can promote peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.15,0:26:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following video,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.24,0:26:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Kenneth Cook of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.78,0:26:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,will explain how this convention program
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.16,0:26:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.58,0:26:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.96,0:26:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can say that we really appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.50,0:26:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your attending\Nthis “Pursue Peace”! Convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.38,0:26:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we love the serene setting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.39,0:26:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,here at our world headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.43,0:27:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on Blue Lake in New York State.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.56,0:27:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, the water is as smooth as a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.15,0:27:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We occasionally see eagles and hawks fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.98,0:27:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the fall of the year\Nwhen the leaves change color,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.57,0:27:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the forest can look spectacular.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.16,0:27:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,More important\Nthan this tranquil setting, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.45,0:27:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is the abundant peace
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.50,0:27:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah has given to his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.08,0:27:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We can say this because of the peace\Nand harmony that unite us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.88,0:27:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what our nationality,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.92,0:27:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,language, race, tribe,\Nor social background is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.59,0:27:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is truly spectacular,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.43,0:27:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when we consider\Nall the turmoil in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.14,0:27:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and how divided people are
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.31,0:27:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,politically, socially, and religiously.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.40,0:27:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we cannot take\Nour beautiful peace for granted;
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.03,0:27:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not maintained automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.99,0:28:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us personally must pursue peace
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.28,0:28:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to have God’s approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.83,0:28:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah certainly wants his worshippers\Nto enjoy lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.79,0:28:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was true in ancient times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.00,0:28:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,God told Moses to have the priests in Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.21,0:28:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,bless the people with very reassuring words.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.18,0:28:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice these words that we find
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.60,0:28:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at Numbers 6:24-26,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.60,0:28:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and hear what the priests\Nwere to say to the people:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.85,0:28:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“May Jehovah bless you and safeguard you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.53,0:28:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“May Jehovah make his face shine upon you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.70,0:28:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“and may he favor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.82,0:28:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“May Jehovah lift up his face toward you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.78,0:28:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and grant you peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.00,0:28:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The next verse states:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.25,0:28:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“And they must place my name
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.25,0:28:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“upon the people of Israel,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.25,0:28:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that I may bless them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.30,0:28:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has placed his name on us too,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.80,0:28:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is richly blessing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.72,0:29:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider what\Nthis convention program is going to cover
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.55,0:29:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’ll know how we can continue
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.22,0:29:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy God’s blessing of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.48,0:29:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we’ll consider\Nhow to be at peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.40,0:29:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our greatest peace comes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.44,0:29:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from having\Na personal relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.57,0:29:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Making him our best Friend benefits us
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.70,0:29:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and leads to peace\Nin every other aspect of our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.66,0:29:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we reach out\Nfor a close relationship with God?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.04,0:29:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We need more\Nthan a superficial knowledge of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.75,0:29:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to get to know Jehovah as a person
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.13,0:29:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and admire his qualities and ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.09,0:29:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can love what he loves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.85,0:29:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and hate what he hates.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.68,0:29:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,During this program,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.68,0:29:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,listen for details about Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.06,0:29:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that will draw you ever closer to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.02,0:30:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we’ll consider\Nhow to be at peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.45,0:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our homes should be havens\Nfor peace for our families.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.99,0:30:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This means more than the absence of arguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.87,0:30:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It involves putting the interests\Nof our family members ahead of our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.87,0:30:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ll learn from this program,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.42,0:30:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that includes showing love\Nand respect to one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.84,0:30:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,working as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.84,0:30:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,improving family communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.34,0:30:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and worshipping Jehovah together.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.06,0:30:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, we’ll consider
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.31,0:30:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how to be at peace despite trials
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.56,0:30:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and troublesome world conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.48,0:30:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,During this convention,\Nwe’re going to tour the world to see how,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.03,0:30:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,despite opposition, illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.57,0:30:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,economic problems, and natural disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.95,0:30:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers really care for one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.12,0:30:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,how they receive help\Nfrom Jehovah’s organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.58,0:30:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they continue\Ntheir spiritual activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.25,0:31:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what may threaten\Nour lives or livelihood,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.30,0:31:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be confident\Nthat Jehovah can help us get through it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.47,0:31:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and retain our peace of mind and heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.01,0:31:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourth, we’ll consider
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.18,0:31:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how to enjoy peace eternally.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Once God’s Kingdom\Nhas lifted mankind to perfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.48,0:31:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll no longer have to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.28,0:31:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As Psalm 72:7 promises:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.15,0:31:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“The righteous will flourish,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.41,0:31:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and peace will abound\Nuntil the moon is no more.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.45,0:31:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there will be peace forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.87,0:31:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This program will help us
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.29,0:31:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to anticipate future blessings from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.96,0:31:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see why “Pursue Peace!”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.34,0:31:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was well chosen\Nas the theme for this year’s convention?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.47,0:31:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To pursue something means
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.64,0:31:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to chase it in order to capture it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.02,0:31:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the influence of Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.52,0:31:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,his wicked world, and our own imperfections,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.90,0:32:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is constantly trying to elude us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.98,0:32:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we have to chase after it\Nto capture it in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.53,0:32:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This convention program will help us do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.41,0:32:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,May the God of peace\Nbe with all of you now and forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.41,0:32:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the heartfelt wish\Nof all of us on the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.42,0:32:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because we love you dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.26,0:32:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the entire convention program!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.72,0:32:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We warmly thank Brother Cook\Nfor highlighting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.52,0:32:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the ways\Nthis convention program
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.23,0:32:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.94,0:32:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s briefly preview
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.69,0:32:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the convention program that is coming our way
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.95,0:32:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been provided by the God of peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.66,0:32:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you may want to follow along\Nby using your copy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.04,0:32:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the convention program.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.66,0:33:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll note that day one has the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.33,0:33:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah will bless his people with peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.38,0:33:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The first symposium will illustrate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.46,0:33:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,how love for God, love for neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.59,0:33:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and love for God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.59,0:33:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lead to genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.26,0:33:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This year’s dramatic Bible reading
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.81,0:33:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on the life of Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.89,0:33:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you will see,\NJacob gives us an excellent example
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.90,0:33:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as to how we can\N“pursue the things
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.99,0:33:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,making for peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.45,0:33:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereafter, we’ll have the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.37,0:33:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Result of True Righteousness\NWill Be Peace,”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.62,0:33:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll see in that talk\Nhow we can resist temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.63,0:33:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as a lion devours prey\Nand assimilates it into his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan tries to get us\Nto succumb to temptations
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.84,0:33:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he can devour us\Nand assimilate us into his world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.35,0:34:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But during that talk,\Nwe’ll learn how to reject his temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.35,0:34:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in the second half of day one,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.06,0:34:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll enjoy our second convention symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.57,0:34:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take Delight in God’s Promises of Peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.15,0:34:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be greatly heartened\Nby Jehovah’s promises of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.66,0:34:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,found in the book of Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, one of the talks has the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.41,0:34:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Wolf and the Lamb Will Feed Together.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.54,0:34:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we can’t even imagine\Nfeeding a wolf and a lamb together.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.30,0:34:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If we tried such, it would likely result
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.05,0:34:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in lamb chops for the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.47,0:34:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah’s promise in Isaiah assures us
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.48,0:34:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that peace will exist\Nbetween humans and animals
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.52,0:34:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and between animals and other animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.11,0:34:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The third convention symposium\Nhas a thought-provoking theme
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.07,0:34:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.41,0:35:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll learn how, despite challenges,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.20,0:35:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,marriage mates, parents, and children
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.46,0:35:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can successfully follow\Nthat road map to family peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.17,0:35:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we’ll enjoy the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.59,0:35:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Loyally Support the ‘Prince of Peace.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.88,0:35:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That talk will remind us
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.89,0:35:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the importance\Nof maintaining our neutrality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.64,0:35:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by not taking sides on political issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.48,0:35:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude day one,\Nwe’ll have the intriguing talk
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.35,0:35:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do Not Be Misled by Imitation Peace!”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.23,0:35:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It will contrast the world’s so-called peace
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.20,0:35:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a genuine peace
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.20,0:35:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus will give his followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.24,0:35:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But then on day two,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.24,0:35:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.33,0:35:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be found . . . spotless\Nand unblemished and in peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.33,0:35:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The second day starts with a symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.67,0:35:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to invigorate us for our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.59,0:35:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can be ready
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.59,0:36:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to share the good news of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.22,0:36:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That will be followed by the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.77,0:36:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Young People\N—Choose a Path That Leads to Peace!”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.77,0:36:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that talk will encourage\Nour dear young ones
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.69,0:36:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue the full-time ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.07,0:36:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to say to you dear young ones
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.20,0:36:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you do this,\Nyou will enjoy a happy life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.03,0:36:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.79,0:36:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we will see a video
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.37,0:36:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that shows how our brothers around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.62,0:36:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are continuing their spiritual activity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.75,0:36:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and are enjoying peace\Ndespite difficult trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.67,0:36:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a highlight of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.89,0:36:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,will be the baptism\Nof new disciples of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.22,0:36:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the baptism talk, the baptism candidates
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.52,0:36:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will be encouraged\Nto “Go On Walking ‘in the Way of Peace.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.52,0:36:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.23,0:36:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is truly the best way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.69,0:37:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Two more symposiums\Nwill use video dramatizations
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.28,0:37:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to contrast traits of peace wreckers
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.45,0:37:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,with the qualities of peacemakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.33,0:37:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a stark contrast between the two\Nyou’ll see in these symposiums!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.34,0:37:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s kind of like the contrast\Nbetween bitter and sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.59,0:37:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Part 1 of this year’s Bible drama
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.18,0:37:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,will remind us of ancient examples\Nof God’s people who pursued peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.18,0:37:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll definitely be able\Nto relate to their examples
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.44,0:37:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and relate it\Nto our current situation in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.61,0:37:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The day will conclude with showing us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.40,0:37:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how to “Safeguard\NOur ‘Uniting Bond of Peace’!”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.78,0:37:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how we can do so
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.78,0:37:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by putting the application\Nof Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.70,0:37:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,always ahead\Nof following local culture and traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.29,0:37:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now on day three, the theme is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.46,0:37:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“May the God who gives hope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.67,0:38:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,fill you with all joy and peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.01,0:38:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The opening symposium\Nwill examine seven examples
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.51,0:38:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of ones who sowed peace and reaped peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.81,0:38:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We will examine Joseph and his brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.23,0:38:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Gibeonites, Gideon, Abigail,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.52,0:38:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mephibosheth, Paul and Barnabas,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.53,0:38:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and modern examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.78,0:38:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We truly hope that many accept our invitation\Nto hear the enlightening
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.24,0:38:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,public Bible discourse
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.25,0:38:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled “Friendship With God\N—How Possible?”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.25,0:38:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.25,0:38:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re not born as friends of God
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.34,0:38:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because we’re born\Nas sinful offspring of Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.55,0:38:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, if you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.55,0:38:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re born as enemies of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.68,0:38:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you’ll hear\Npeople say of a little baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.60,0:38:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look at that little angel,”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.18,0:38:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but more accurate would be to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.06,0:38:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look at that little enemy of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.19,0:39:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, we love that little baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.19,0:39:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s not hopeless\Nbecause our loving Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.82,0:39:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,has made reconciliation with him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.07,0:39:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,within the reach of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.16,0:39:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We can become a good friend of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.75,0:39:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that close relationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.29,0:39:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will become our most valuable possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.21,0:39:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But then after we enjoy\NPart 2 of the Bible drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.26,0:39:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the concluding talk of this convention
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.93,0:39:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,will fill our hearts with a joyful prospect
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.26,0:39:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that “Universal Peace Is Sure to Come!”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.27,0:39:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s guaranteed by the God “who cannot lie.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.73,0:39:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we’ll join in singing\Na beautiful new original song
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.94,0:39:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll close with a prayer of praise\Nto Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.82,0:39:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the Source of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.37,0:39:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, dear brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.37,0:39:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a brief synopsis
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.66,0:39:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of our wonderful three-day convention
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.33,0:40:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,provided by the God of peace\Nthat is coming our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.00,0:40:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And throughout,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.00,0:40:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the program will be enhanced\Nwith dozens of videos,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.26,0:40:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll see our brothers\Neither in real-life settings
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.22,0:40:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or dramatizations\Nthat we’ll definitely be able to relate to.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.23,0:40:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the following video
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.94,0:40:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is a little, or small, sampling of the videos
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.69,0:40:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see during this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.90,0:40:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.11,0:40:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.28,0:40:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.57,0:40:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Today’s poll: Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.58,0:40:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she would never; she’s an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.54,0:40:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to go up to the girls\Nand smash their phones.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.00,0:40:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral?\NAin’t no neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.00,0:40:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.17,0:40:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.34,0:40:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What I was feeling back then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.30,0:40:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was just sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.42,0:40:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,never really peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.84,0:40:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.76,0:40:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley from DeNure Design here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.39,0:40:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there just a little bit of envy in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.60,0:40:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In June of 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.52,0:41:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge group of armed men came to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.73,0:41:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They represented the ideals of my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.24,0:41:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea\Nwhat this is going to cost us?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.24,0:41:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t have a choice.\NYou went behind my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.91,0:41:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where’s your mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.08,0:41:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how many people\Nhave actually gotten sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.54,0:41:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.87,0:41:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what always happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.96,0:41:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re just\Nabout to lose all your strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.88,0:41:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does that something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.55,0:41:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so grateful that we made peace
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.76,0:41:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,before the world turned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.68,0:41:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s an important question\Nfor all of us:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.93,0:41:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we prepare our heart
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.69,0:41:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to receive God’s peace\Nduring this convention?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.86,0:41:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezra 7:10 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.24,0:41:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘Ezra prepared his heart\Nto consult the Law of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.24,0:41:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and to practice it,\Nand to teach it to the Israelites.’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.20,0:42:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what was the result?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.96,0:42:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 11 tells us\Nhe became “an expert in the study
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.59,0:42:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of the commandments of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.51,0:42:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in imitation of Ezra,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.97,0:42:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we prepare our heart
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.84,0:42:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for what we’re going to take in\Nat this convention?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.81,0:42:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing (very important),\Nby prayer and meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.94,0:42:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make sure that our heart is ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.73,0:42:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,receptive to receive Jehovah’s instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.57,0:42:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can also make sure that in our heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.65,0:42:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we are determined\Nto apply what Jehovah teaches us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.95,0:42:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But then another thing we can do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.95,0:42:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is we can pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.08,0:42:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to the music-video presentations
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.92,0:42:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be shown before every session\Nas the convention begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.04,0:42:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these presentations\Nhave been carefully crafted
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.97,0:42:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to help prepare our heart for each session.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.51,0:42:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Much time, effort, and expense
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.47,0:43:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,has been expended in preparing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.35,0:43:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,these beautiful presentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.81,0:43:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So please listen carefully\Nas the sounds and scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.61,0:43:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,prepare your heart to accept\Nthe spiritual instruction
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.95,0:43:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.95,0:43:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, may each of us be determined
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.41,0:43:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen attentively
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.29,0:43:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to what Jehovah is teaching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.83,0:43:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,May we be determined to imitate the psalmist
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.54,0:43:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who humbly stated at Psalm 85:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.88,0:43:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will listen\Nto what the true God Jehovah says,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.89,0:43:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for he will speak peace to his people.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.81,0:43:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do, we will learn\Nhow to pursue peace with all people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.81,0:43:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to the praise of Jehovah, the God of peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.77,0:43:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,who blesses his people with peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.61,0:43:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we will be successful in pursuing peace
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.15,0:43:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,until we no longer have to pursue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.53,0:44:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what do we mean?\NWell, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.33,0:44:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Jehovah have to pursue peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.08,0:44:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he have to chase it\Nin an effort to try to catch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.83,0:44:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.21,0:44:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah merely displays peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.67,0:44:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the new world,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.67,0:44:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what a wonderful time it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.13,0:44:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when we no longer have to pursue peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.22,0:44:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but like Jehovah,\Nwe can merely display peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.02,0:44:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, let’s be determined\Nto continue to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.02,0:44:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And may this wonderful convention
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.77,0:44:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that is coming our way help us to do so!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.61,0:44:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lett, for helping us\Nprepare our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.41,0:44:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,for the rest of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.41,0:44:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We are ready for Jehovah to teach us\Nhow to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.04,0:44:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How is peace related to love?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.26,0:44:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we show love?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.26,0:45:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And what blessings result when we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.93,0:45:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The first symposium of this convention\Nwill answer those questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.60,0:45:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Seth Hyatt,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.60,0:45:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Service Committee\Nof the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.85,0:45:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will begin with the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.86,0:45:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace\N—Love for God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.45,0:45:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.75,0:45:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a connection, a relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.87,0:45:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,between love and peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.34,0:45:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, what role does love play
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.72,0:45:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in achieving genuine peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.80,0:45:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible helps us to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.47,0:45:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that love is an essential element
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.52,0:45:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in achieving genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.90,0:45:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re interested in showing love.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As students of the Bible, we know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.32,0:46:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that humans were created\Nin the image of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.20,0:46:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result,\Nyou and I have the ability to show love.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.25,0:46:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But we also know that we live in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.50,0:46:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that has a very distorted view
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.59,0:46:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and definition of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.09,0:46:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That, combined with our own imperfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.09,0:46:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,means that if we’re not careful,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.47,0:46:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,our view of love can become distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.31,0:46:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do we guard against that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.10,0:46:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,By allowing Jehovah to teach us how to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.19,0:46:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you think about it,\Nwhat better teacher could we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.20,0:46:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says that “God is love.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.91,0:46:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that Jehovah, our Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.70,0:46:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—who knows us better than we know ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.41,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who embodies, who personifies love—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.00,0:47:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is willing to teach us how to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.21,0:47:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.26,0:47:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by means of his Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.14,0:47:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and by means of his own beautiful example.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.64,0:47:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get acquainted with Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.39,0:47:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn what love really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.69,0:47:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we put that love to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.23,0:47:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus did,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.49,0:47:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,then we’re in a position
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.15,0:47:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.29,0:47:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to explore how love for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.54,0:47:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,love of neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.54,0:47:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and love for God’s Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.34,0:47:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can lead to genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.88,0:47:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s talk about love for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.64,0:47:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How important is that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.81,0:47:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if we want to enjoy genuine peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.68,0:47:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jesus provides some insight\Nin a statement he made
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.06,0:48:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s recorded in our Bibles\Nat Matthew chapter 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.32,0:48:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.65,0:48:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.74,0:48:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to read verse 37.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.41,0:48:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to provide some context for these words,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.95,0:48:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus has been asked a question by a man
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.91,0:48:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who is well-versed in the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.63,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“[What] is the greatest commandment\Nin the Law?”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.09,0:48:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Jesus responds:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.47,0:48:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to him:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.84,0:48:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You must love Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.14,0:48:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘with your whole heart
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.14,0:48:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and with your whole soul
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.52,0:48:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“and with your whole mind.’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.31,0:48:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the greatest and first commandment.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.82,0:48:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love Jehovah your God”\N—a command.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.53,0:48:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Love for Jehovah is essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.99,0:48:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be\Nthe most important relationship in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.29,0:49:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More important than any human,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.00,0:49:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,more important than any thing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.13,0:49:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—we want to love Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.59,0:49:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To what extent?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.38,0:49:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jesus says: “with your whole heart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.01,0:49:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that involve?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.39,0:49:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of Jesus’ words
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.27,0:49:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to understand that he was talking\Nabout a person’s feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.02,0:49:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,emotions, desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.07,0:49:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So does love for God involve our emotions?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.53,0:49:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.78,0:49:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has to involve more\Nthan a simple affection for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.58,0:49:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.21,0:49:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jesus say next?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.46,0:49:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“With your whole soul,”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.63,0:49:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, with your entire being.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.71,0:49:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We use everything we have
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.51,0:49:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to praise Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.68,0:49:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and to prove our love for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.77,0:50:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But even more is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.23,0:50:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus concludes by saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.48,0:50:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“with your whole mind.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.61,0:50:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So our intellectual faculties are involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.36,0:50:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re willing to take the time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.95,0:50:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to know Jehovah’s thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.16,0:50:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.74,0:50:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to think the way Jehovah thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.79,0:50:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to understand his purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.92,0:50:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and his requirements for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.88,0:50:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to understand his personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.51,0:50:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we think about that kind of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.05,0:50:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s clear that it encompasses
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.64,0:50:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,our thoughts, our words, and our actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.27,0:50:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.69,0:50:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that kind of love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.28,0:50:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,provides a basis for a friendship with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.70,0:51:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that results in peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.33,0:51:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we see the progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.79,0:51:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Loving Jehovah with our whole heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.17,0:51:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,soul, and mind
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.30,0:51:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.51,0:51:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we enjoy peace with God,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.47,0:51:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we can also enjoy inner peace
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.22,0:51:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and peace with those around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.14,0:51:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how does that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.40,0:51:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, our love for Jehovah\Nmotivates us to imitate him,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.94,0:51:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and we cultivate the qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.78,0:51:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah displays,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.57,0:51:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for example: patience,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.37,0:51:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,kindness, mildness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.04,0:51:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—qualities that make us attractive to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.75,0:51:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and qualities that promote peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.01,0:51:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you would agree
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.13,0:51:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to be at peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.51,0:52:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes our peace can be threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.98,0:52:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We may experience pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.81,0:52:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be the subject of some wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.90,0:52:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,some injustice, some evil
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.03,0:52:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that threatens our peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.12,0:52:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the question is this:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.91,0:52:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we handle things in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.46,0:52:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that is pleasing to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.17,0:52:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or will we become impatient
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.34,0:52:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or try to take matters into our own hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.09,0:52:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.30,0:52:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how a family draws strength\Nfrom a Bible account
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.68,0:52:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that highlights love and respect
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.64,0:52:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.12,0:53:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.33,0:53:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.54,0:53:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, you’re going to be late for school!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.72,0:53:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.59,0:53:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, Mom. I’m going to preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.22,0:53:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.43,0:53:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.97,0:53:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Mom. Love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.39,0:53:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.77,0:53:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.20,0:53:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Today’s poll: Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.99,0:53:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She would never; she’s an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.08,0:53:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s all a front.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.70,0:53:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know she’s wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.95,0:53:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.50,0:53:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she totally just saw us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.16,0:53:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I’m totally posting that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.17,0:53:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.00,0:53:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. It’s up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.59,0:53:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.84,0:53:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you just get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.59,0:53:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.30,0:53:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.38,0:54:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.13,0:54:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the craziest.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.93,0:54:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.64,0:54:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, Brooke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.72,0:54:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Amanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.43,0:54:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.97,0:54:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.10,0:54:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s Jake.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.60,0:54:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Today’s poll: Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.90,0:54:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she would never; she’s an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.82,0:54:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s all an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.28,0:54:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know she’s wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.11,0:54:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, she saw us.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.07,0:54:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She saw us.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.12,0:54:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.16,0:54:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to comment?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.41,0:54:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.33,0:54:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t even think she likes guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.08,0:54:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What if she’s into girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.25,0:54:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.08,0:54:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Comments!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.75,0:54:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is getting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.92,0:54:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet she’s still a virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.48,0:54:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, can I see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.23,0:54:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.02,0:54:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.94,0:55:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s16}{nArial}Enjoy Life Forever! 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.11,0:55:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how are you going to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.57,0:55:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s a very good question, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.32,0:55:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, God promises . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.11,0:55:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, not God, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.82,0:55:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.99,0:55:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? Well, I try to help others . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.12,0:55:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Try?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.37,0:55:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, all you do\Nis stand next to your little cart
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.66,0:55:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,while the rest of us\Nstand up for your rights, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.21,0:55:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m actually neutral when it . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.21,0:55:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.84,0:55:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain’t no neutral. You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.59,0:55:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.73,0:55:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.40,0:55:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a tough day at the cart, but I’m OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.96,0:55:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, Brooke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.96,0:56:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And Amanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.63,0:56:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.17,0:56:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.88,0:56:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.09,0:56:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.35,0:56:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, Brooke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.48,0:56:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Amanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.19,0:56:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.98,0:56:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.90,0:56:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s Jake.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.49,0:56:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Today’s poll: Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.74,0:56:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she would never; she’s an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.12,0:56:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s all an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.33,0:56:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know she’s wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.54,0:56:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, she saw us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.63,0:56:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so sorry that happened to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.64,0:56:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.35,0:56:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it reminds me of a situation Paul was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.11,0:57:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was at Acts chapter 16
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.07,0:57:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 23:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.74,0:57:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“After they had inflicted many blows on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.00,0:57:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“they threw them into prison
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.17,0:57:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and ordered the jailer\Nto guard them securely.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.09,0:57:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because he got such an order, he threw them
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.80,0:57:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“into the inner prison
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.81,0:57:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“and fastened their feet in the stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.52,0:57:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“But about the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.02,0:57:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Paul and Silas were praying
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.11,0:57:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“and praising God with song,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.28,0:57:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the prisoners were listening to them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.07,0:57:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think made them want to sing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.25,0:58:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They loved Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.00,0:58:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they focused on that,\Nhow do you think they felt?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.76,0:58:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.47,0:58:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they felt some peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.51,0:58:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.77,0:58:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we dig a little bit deeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.89,0:58:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.60,0:58:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.69,0:58:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.82,0:58:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabe and Olivia are under pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.82,0:58:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—Olivia in the classroom,\NGabe at the witnessing cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.83,0:58:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How will they handle the pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.12,0:58:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that preserves\Ntheir peace with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.46,0:58:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.13,0:58:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And really, all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.93,0:58:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,need to reflect on that question
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.72,0:59:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re under pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.39,0:59:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that Jehovah’s way is the best way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.60,0:59:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re convinced that his way of ruling\Nis the best way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.23,0:59:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we’re subjected to pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.20,0:59:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps the victim of some injustice
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.87,0:59:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or even of some evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.83,0:59:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we may be inclined\Nto take matters into our own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.29,0:59:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.30,0:59:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it can jeopardize our peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.97,0:59:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do we demonstrate respect
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.22,0:59:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s sovereignty?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.93,0:59:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspired advice\Nin Romans chapter 12 can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.06,0:59:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look together at Romans chapter 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.40,0:59:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning in verse 17:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.07,0:59:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Return evil for evil to no one.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.74,1:00:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this provides the context\Nfor what follows.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.75,1:00:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We may suffer some evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.88,1:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Return evil for evil to no one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.13,1:00:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Take into consideration what is fine\Nfrom the viewpoint of all men.”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.01,1:00:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then notice verse 18:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.47,1:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“If possible, as far as it depends
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.51,1:00:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“on you,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.06,1:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,be peaceable (be a peacemaker)\Nwith all men.”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.90,1:00:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these words
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.94,1:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,really heighten our appreciation
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.07,1:00:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s reasonableness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.53,1:00:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.41,1:00:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah doesn’t ask us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.45,1:00:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to do something that we can’t do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.37,1:00:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t ask us to control others.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.17,1:00:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.26,1:01:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the extent “it depends on you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.22,1:01:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah asks that each of us
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.89,1:01:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,control ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.47,1:01:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our response to a situation,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.35,1:01:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be peacemakers.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.77,1:01:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then an explanation, verse 19:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.49,1:01:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not avenge yourselves, beloved,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.07,1:01:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but yield place to the wrath.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.58,1:01:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.54,1:01:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it is written: ‘Vengeance is mine;
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.41,1:01:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I will repay,’ says Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.96,1:01:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the advice is this:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.46,1:01:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Be a peacemaker,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.59,1:01:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave wrath to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.09,1:01:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him determine\Nif and when and upon whom
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.72,1:01:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,vengeance will be brought.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.69,1:01:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easy to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.98,1:01:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but is it always easy to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.40,1:01:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.40,1:01:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The example of King David
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.61,1:02:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,can be very helpful to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.07,1:02:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Through no fault of his own,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.08,1:02:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,David became the target
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.08,1:02:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of King Saul’s murderous hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.42,1:02:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And on several occasions,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.63,1:02:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Saul tried to kill David.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.96,1:02:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For several years David lived as a fugitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.84,1:02:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were opportunities during that time
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.89,1:02:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for David to harm Saul, even to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.98,1:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have justified that in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.90,1:02:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you think had he done so
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.48,1:02:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have threatened his peace
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.40,1:02:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—his peace, especially, with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.16,1:02:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that it would.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.37,1:02:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did David respond?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.37,1:02:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,On one occasion, he said to his men:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.25,1:02:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is unthinkable from Jehovah’s standpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.59,1:03:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I should do such a thing to my lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.30,1:03:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the anointed of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.97,1:03:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped David?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.76,1:03:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he saw a bigger picture
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.22,1:03:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,than David and Saul, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.60,1:03:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw a picture with David, Saul,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.02,1:03:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.07,1:03:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that if Saul needed to be corrected,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.61,1:03:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would do it in his time and way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.78,1:03:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, David was willing to be patient
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.70,1:03:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and he preserved his peace
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.29,1:03:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—his peace with God, his inner peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.13,1:03:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and his peace with those around him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.00,1:03:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful example!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.59,1:03:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be sure that if we demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.93,1:03:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,our love for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.10,1:03:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by respecting his sovereignty\Nand waiting on him,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.97,1:03:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we will enjoy peace as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.44,1:03:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah assures us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.44,1:04:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will bless his people
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.57,1:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will bless us with peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.90,1:04:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So let us be determined to love Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.53,1:04:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with our whole heart, soul, and mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.24,1:04:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and to demonstrate our love for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.37,1:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by patiently waiting on him\Nand respecting his sovereignty
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.00,1:04:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—his way of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.05,1:04:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do, we will enjoy
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.26,1:04:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the incomparable peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.84,1:04:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Brother Ralph Walls,\Na helper to the Personnel Committee,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.97,1:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will present the next talk of this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.56,1:04:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace\N—Love of Neighbor.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.66,1:04:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Foretelling dominant traits\Nthat would exist in the last days,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.33,1:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Timothy chapter 3 says\Nthat “men will be lovers of themselves.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.96,1:05:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong for us to love ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.54,1:05:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it’s normal, even necessary,\Nto have a healthy love of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.51,1:05:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.05,1:05:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love your neighbor as yourself.”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.31,1:05:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll talk more about that in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.85,1:05:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the love mentioned here
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.85,1:05:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is distorted and selfish.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.07,1:05:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it prevents love of neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.99,1:05:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes a barrier to peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.86,1:05:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Bible scholars suggest that Paul\Nput love of self at the top of his list
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.83,1:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Timothy 3:1-5
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.87,1:05:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because all the remaining\Nnegative characteristics in the list
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.54,1:05:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,result from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.54,1:05:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And those traits too are a barrier to peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.34,1:05:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\N“not [being] open to any agreement”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.64,1:05:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned at 2 Timothy 3:3,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.39,1:05:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,often leads to “anger, wrath,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.48,1:06:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,screaming, and abusive speech.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.19,1:06:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than bringing peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.36,1:06:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,such a lack of self-control\N“stirs up strife.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.61,1:06:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, love of neighbor
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.28,1:06:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,has the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.41,1:06:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads to genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.08,1:06:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn to Matthew chapter 22,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.42,1:06:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 36.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.09,1:06:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the Pharisees versed in the Law
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.92,1:06:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,tests Jesus:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.84,1:06:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“Teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.01,1:06:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the greatest commandment\Nin the Law?”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.18,1:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus responded with the words in verse 37
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.23,1:06:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,just considered at length\Nin the preceding talk:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.23,1:06:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love Jehovah your God.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.74,1:06:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, Jesus goes\Nbeyond the original question
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.91,1:06:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and quotes a second commandment.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.74,1:06:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 39:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.79,1:07:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“The second, like it, is this:
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.71,1:07:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You must love your neighbor as yourself.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.21,1:07:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is saying that the two commandments
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.55,1:07:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—love of God and love of neighbor—
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.47,1:07:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are linked.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.64,1:07:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how exactly would you define “neighbor”?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.35,1:07:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn to Luke chapter 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.85,1:07:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Jesus answered this very question:
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.57,1:07:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who really is my neighbor?”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.36,1:07:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus responds clearly\Nwith his renowned illustration
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.49,1:07:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the neighborly Samaritan.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.78,1:07:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In Jesus’ day, the Jews disdained Samaritans.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.66,1:07:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Their attitude moved Jesus\Nto make a powerful point.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.37,1:07:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In his illustration,\NJesus said that the Samaritan
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.59,1:07:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,took extraordinary measures\Nto help a Jewish man.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.72,1:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jew had fallen victim to robbers,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.64,1:07:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and his own countrymen ignored him
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.72,1:08:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—leaving him half-dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.27,1:08:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What Jesus said\Nmust have stunned the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.31,1:08:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 10:33, 34 reads:
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.15,1:08:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“But a certain Samaritan
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.69,1:08:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“traveling the road came upon him,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.28,1:08:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“and at seeing him, he was moved with pity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.53,1:08:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“So he approached him\Nand bandaged his wounds,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.87,1:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“pouring oil and wine on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.75,1:08:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he mounted him on his own animal\Nand brought him to an inn
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.75,1:08:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and took care of him.”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.47,1:08:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus then asked a penetrating question\Nin verse 36:
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.14,1:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who of these three
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.14,1:08:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to you\Nto have made himself neighbor?”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.14,1:08:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,His words recorded in verse 37
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.15,1:08:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,are also directed to you and to me:
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.90,1:08:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go and do the same yourself.”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.53,1:09:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our neighbors include
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.62,1:09:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,not only our family members\Nand our Christian brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.25,1:09:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but all whom we encounter from day to day.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.42,1:09:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, our love
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.92,1:09:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,extends to those who are not of our own race,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.51,1:09:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tribe, nationality, or religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.63,1:09:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we show that love?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.68,1:09:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn with me to Romans chapter 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.81,1:09:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we love our neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.98,1:09:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we avoid conduct that disrupts peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.28,1:09:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we strive to apply\Nthe inspired counsel
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.95,1:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 13:8-10:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.20,1:09:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not owe anything to anyone\Nexcept to love one another;
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.08,1:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“for whoever loves his fellow man\Nhas fulfilled the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.96,1:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the law code,\N‘You must not commit adultery,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.17,1:10:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“you must not murder,\Nyou must not steal, you must not covet,’
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.43,1:10:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“and whatever other commandment there is,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.51,1:10:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“is summed up in this saying:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.14,1:10:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You must love your neighbor as yourself.’
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.48,1:10:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Love does not work evil to one’s neighbor;
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.98,1:10:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, love is the law’s fulfillment.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.03,1:10:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that our responsibility\Nis to treat others
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.20,1:10:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways that promote peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.74,1:10:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When others treat us unkindly,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.04,1:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we endeavor to imitate Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.00,1:10:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was being insulted,\Nhe did not return the insult.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.75,1:10:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was suffering,\Nhe didn’t go threatening.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.17,1:10:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitating the Prince of Peace\Nand the God of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.84,1:10:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.26,1:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.27,1:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how a family benefits\Nfrom the apostle Paul’s example
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.31,1:10:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of displaying love of neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.35,1:10:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,even when provoked.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.36,1:10:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.36,1:10:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.98,1:11:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, all you do\Nis stand next to your little cart.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.49,1:11:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.24,1:11:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.86,1:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just stand next to your little cart.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.61,1:11:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.95,1:11:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain’t no neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.66,1:11:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up for your rights.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.37,1:11:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.49,1:11:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabe,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.83,1:11:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened today?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.16,1:11:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just that I’ve been yelled at\Nin service before, but
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.34,1:11:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this time I wanted to—I don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.13,1:11:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to go up to the girls\Nand smash their phones.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.64,1:11:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so glad that you didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.56,1:11:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.85,1:11:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.73,1:11:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was like—I was like so angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.03,1:11:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.11,1:11:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s keep reading.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.95,1:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We had left off in verse 26.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.04,1:12:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Suddenly a great earthquake occurred,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.04,1:12:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that the foundations of the jail\Nwere shaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.26,1:12:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“Moreover, all the doors\Nwere instantly opened,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.01,1:12:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and everyone’s bonds came loose.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.55,1:12:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“When the jailer woke up\Nand saw that the prison doors were open,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.93,1:12:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“he drew his sword
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.98,1:12:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“and was about to kill himself,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.06,1:12:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“assuming that the prisoners had escaped.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.52,1:12:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“But Paul called out with a loud voice:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.07,1:12:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do not hurt yourself, for we are all here!’
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.78,1:12:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“So he asked for lights and rushed in,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.87,1:12:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“and seized with trembling,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.08,1:12:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he fell down before Paul and Silas.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.63,1:12:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think about what the jailer\Nhad done to Paul.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.09,1:12:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have hated him for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.68,1:12:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he could have.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.97,1:12:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I guess he saw the jailer’s pain\Ninstead of just his own.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.07,1:13:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Paul loved his neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.19,1:13:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t hold back\Nfrom trying to save his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.58,1:13:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.59,1:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how do you have the nerve\Nto keep coming out here?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.72,1:13:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you were right
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.31,1:13:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about what you said.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.39,1:13:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No one should stand around\Nwhile other people suffer injustice.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.19,1:13:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So do something. Fight like we do.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.02,1:13:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my way of making a difference
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.02,1:13:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—the only way that I know\Nthe world can really change.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.32,1:13:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, man, the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.07,1:13:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I get what you’re thinking,\Nbut let me show you just one scripture.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.08,1:13:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, one scripture.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.74,1:13:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a verse in the Bible\Nthat convinced me
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.04,1:14:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of how I can make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.08,1:14:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s at Matthew 24:14.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.88,1:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it says:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.63,1:14:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this good news of the Kingdom\Nwill be preached
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.63,1:14:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“in all the inhabited earth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.88,1:14:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“for a witness to all the nations,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.14,1:14:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the end will come.”
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.23,1:14:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the dramatization, Paul could have reacted
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.61,1:14:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in a negative way toward the jailer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.61,1:14:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in spite of the way\Nhe had been treated,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.28,1:14:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he displayed neighborly love.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.32,1:14:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this had a powerful effect on the jailer
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.78,1:14:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought praise to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.37,1:14:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we are imperfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.42,1:14:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we must work hard\Nat cultivating love for our neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.42,1:14:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is illustrated in what happened\Nwith the apostle Peter.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.18,1:14:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to becoming a follower of Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.68,1:15:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he did not have fellowship\Nwith non-Jewish people.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.56,1:15:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But after he became a Christian,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.19,1:15:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God taught him
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.19,1:15:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that division between Jews and Gentiles
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.57,1:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was not to continue,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.78,1:15:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and Peter got the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.36,1:15:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At Acts 10:34, 35,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.66,1:15:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter is quoted as saying:
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.45,1:15:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now I truly understand\Nthat God is not partial,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.83,1:15:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in every nation the man who fears him\Nand does what is right
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.84,1:15:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is acceptable to him.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.13,1:15:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter even stayed in the newly converted\NGentiles’ home for days.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.89,1:15:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And he continued the practice of eating
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.76,1:15:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with non-Jewish Christians.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.14,1:15:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,However, 13 years later
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.27,1:15:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,while in Syrian Antioch,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.77,1:15:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter suddenly stopped associating\Nwith Gentile Christians.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.57,1:15:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.45,1:15:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He feared the reaction\Nof some Jewish Christians
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.78,1:15:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who were slow to accept change.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.58,1:16:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This illustrates that prejudice\Ncan be deeply rooted.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.04,1:16:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes constant effort\Nto rid ourselves of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.54,1:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must learn to view others impartially
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.75,1:16:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jehovah does.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.13,1:16:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to treat others\Nas Jehovah treats them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.34,1:16:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In his Sermon on the Mount, Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.10,1:16:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“You heard that it was said:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.64,1:16:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You must love your neighbor\Nand hate your enemy.’
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.77,1:16:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“However, I say to you:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.44,1:16:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue to love your enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.57,1:16:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and to pray for those who persecute you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.49,1:16:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as recorded at Matthew chapter 5,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.33,1:16:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 45,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.12,1:16:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he explains why we want to show\Nthat type of love:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.83,1:16:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“So that you may prove yourselves\Nsons of your Father who is in the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.51,1:16:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“since he makes his sun rise\Non both the wicked and the good
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.22,1:17:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and makes it rain on both the righteous
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.30,1:17:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the unrighteous.”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.85,1:17:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This love produced by holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.85,1:17:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is markedly different from the sort of love\Nthat is common in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.86,1:17:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s based on a higher principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.03,1:17:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said even sinners\Nwill follow a policy of like for like.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.82,1:17:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we want to prove ourselves\Nsons of our “Father who is in the heavens,”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.83,1:17:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we must be different.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.16,1:17:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome others
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.96,1:17:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as God and Christ have welcomed us.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.42,1:17:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At Romans 15:7, the Bible says to us:
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.34,1:17:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Welcome one another,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.72,1:17:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Christ also welcomed you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.89,1:17:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greek word used there conveys the idea
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.31,1:17:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of receiving someone kindly or hospitably
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.35,1:17:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as into one’s home\Nor circle of friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.90,1:17:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Prejudice withers as love grows.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.99,1:18:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that at one time,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.45,1:18:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we were all strangers, or foreigners,\Nnot close to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.12,1:18:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah drew us to him
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.25,1:18:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with “cords of love.”
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.83,1:18:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ welcomed us.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.09,1:18:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He opened the door, as it were,\Nso that we could become part of God’s family.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.55,1:18:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Jesus has kindly accepted us
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.26,1:18:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as imperfect as we are,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.77,1:18:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it should be unthinkable for us\Nto reject anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.69,1:18:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.48,1:18:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,divisions, prejudice, and hostility\Nwill doubtless increase in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.49,1:18:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as we approach the end of this wicked system.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.32,1:18:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As servants of Jehovah, though,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.16,1:18:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we seek “the wisdom from above,”\Nwhich is impartial
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.37,1:18:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and promotes peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.87,1:18:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We rejoice
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.00,1:18:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as we forge friendships\Nwith people from other lands,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.51,1:19:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,accept cultural differences,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.51,1:19:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and possibly even learn\Nthe languages of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.43,1:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do this,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.43,1:19:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,peace flows “just like a river”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.81,1:19:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and justice “like the waves of the sea.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.65,1:19:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We “work what is good toward all,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.11,1:19:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but especially [our brothers].”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.03,1:19:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Love of neighbor moves us\Nto make sacrifices in behalf of others
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.36,1:19:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and to share the good news\Nat every opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.62,1:19:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Master, Jesus, said:
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.25,1:19:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is my commandment,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.08,1:19:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you love one another\Njust as I have loved you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.88,1:19:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the blessings\Nthat come from love of neighbor?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.47,1:19:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus answers that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.60,1:19:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at John chapter 15,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.68,1:19:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read verses 8 through 10,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.98,1:20:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning with verse 8.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.44,1:20:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.45,1:20:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“My father is glorified in this,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.66,1:20:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you keep bearing much fruit
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.70,1:20:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove yourselves my disciples.”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.71,1:20:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The second blessing, verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.13,1:20:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just as the Father has loved me,\Nso I have loved you;
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.26,1:20:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“remain in my love.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.97,1:20:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you observe my commandments,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.89,1:20:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will remain in my love,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.68,1:20:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as I have observed\Nthe commandments of the Father
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.98,1:20:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain in his love.”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.61,1:20:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Robert Ciranko,\Na helper to the Writing Committee,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.07,1:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,will now present the final talk\Nof this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.90,1:20:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace\N—Love for God’s Word.”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.63,1:21:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine a collection\Nof some 40 million books?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.38,1:21:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They would fill more than 800 miles,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.55,1:21:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or 1,300 kilometers, of bookshelves?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.55,1:21:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, that is what you can find\Nin what has been described
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.51,1:21:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as the largest library in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.73,1:21:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Library of Congress\Nin Washington, D.C.,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.69,1:21:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.86,1:21:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Which book would you say\Nis the most worthwhile to read
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.32,1:21:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,among all of those millions of volumes?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.94,1:21:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let the apostle Paul\Nanswer that question.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.99,1:21:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In his second letter to Timothy\Nat 2 Timothy 3:15,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.70,1:21:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he referred to “the holy writings,\Nwhich are able to make [us]
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.20,1:21:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,wise for salvation\Nthrough faith in Christ Jesus.”
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.75,1:21:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was referring, of course,\Nto God’s own written Word
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.63,1:21:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that we know as the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.22,1:21:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The contents of this book can give us\Nthe wisdom that we need to gain salvation,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.80,1:21:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and that makes it\Nthe most worthwhile book on earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.73,1:22:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can a book have\Nsuch a profound effect on a person?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.10,1:22:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when describing books\Nand their authors per se,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.15,1:22:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the secular writer Gilbert Highet once stated
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.24,1:22:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that books are not “lumps of lifeless paper,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.32,1:22:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“but minds alive on the shelves.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.66,1:22:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“From each of them goes out\Nits own voice . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.66,1:22:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“So by taking down one of these volumes\Nand opening it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.12,1:22:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“one can call into range\Nthe voice of a man the author,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.63,1:22:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“far distant in time and space,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.96,1:22:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and hear him speaking to us,\Nmind to mind, heart to heart.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.97,1:22:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When we take this book, the Bible,\Ndown off the shelf and open it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.81,1:22:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we are calling into range\Nthe voice of its Author, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.27,1:22:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And is he speaking to us\Nmind to mind, heart to heart?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.65,1:22:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.65,1:22:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, at Jeremiah 29:11,\NJehovah tells us:
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.20,1:22:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“I well know the thoughts\Nthat I am thinking toward you, . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.32,1:22:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“thoughts of peace, and not of calamity,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.79,1:23:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to give you a future and a hope.”
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.25,1:23:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And at Proverbs 27:11, Jehovah tells us:
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.71,1:23:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be wise . . . and make my heart rejoice,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.46,1:23:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can make a reply\Nto him who taunts me.”
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.09,1:23:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How grateful we are\Nthat Jehovah has given us
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.01,1:23:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,his precious Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.43,1:23:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that reveals his intimate thoughts\Nand feelings,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.43,1:23:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that draws us close to him,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.43,1:23:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and that teaches us\Nhow to gain everlasting life!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.48,1:23:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we love Jehovah,\Nwe also love and cherish
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.07,1:23:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what he tells us\Nthrough the pages of his written Word.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.40,1:23:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is exactly how the psalmist felt
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.03,1:23:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who wrote the 119th Psalm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.66,1:23:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your Bible to Psalm 119,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.87,1:23:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and find verse 161.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.46,1:23:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Psalm 119:161.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.67,1:23:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In the latter part, it says:
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.92,1:23:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“But my heart stands in awe of your words.”
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.51,1:24:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now see what more he wrote\Nin verses 167 and 168:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.56,1:24:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“I keep your reminders,\Nand I love them dearly.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.23,1:24:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“I observe your orders and your reminders,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.52,1:24:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for you are aware of all that I do.”
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.28,1:24:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This Bible writer did not view\NGod’s orders and reminders
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.03,1:24:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as just a list of cold, legalistic statutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.91,1:24:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be sure\Nthat he did not consider them
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.58,1:24:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to be burdensome.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.58,1:24:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he knew that they formed the basis
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.75,1:24:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for the best life possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.17,1:24:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is why he not only wanted\Nto learn God’s orders,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.93,1:24:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also desired to observe,\Nor obey, them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.77,1:24:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The psalmist believed that God’s Word\Nis the one thing worth studying,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.77,1:24:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and that because of knowing\NGod’s orders and reminders,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.02,1:24:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we are far wiser than people
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.15,1:24:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who know everything else\Nexcept God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.11,1:25:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now look at what more he wrote in verse 165:
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.04,1:25:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Abundant peace\Nbelongs to those who love your law;
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.42,1:25:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing can make them stumble.”
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.04,1:25:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Herein lies a major reason\Nwhy we love God’s Word:
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.51,1:25:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Abiding by it leads to genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.47,1:25:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone longs for peace in their life,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.89,1:25:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and through the pages of the Bible,\Nwe learn how to attain it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.56,1:25:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we choose to live by God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.65,1:25:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the face of the trials\Nthat arise in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.77,1:25:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—some of which may try to steal away\Nour peace of mind and heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.45,1:25:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, Jehovah knows what we\Nare going through every day of our lives
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.28,1:25:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and stands ready to help us.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.12,1:25:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we love and obey Jehovah’s Word,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.71,1:25:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we will not be stumbled spiritually\Nby what someone else does or says
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.54,1:25:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or by any other matter or situation in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.84,1:26:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But how does love for God’s Word\Nlead to such peace
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.14,1:26:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep us from stumbling?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.39,1:26:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We know\Nthat “all scripture is inspired of God,”
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.93,1:26:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,making the Bible the most reliable guide\Nfor every aspect of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.60,1:26:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, his wisdom\Nis infinitely superior to our own.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.32,1:26:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading the Bible enables us\Nto look at matters
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.86,1:26:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from God’s elevated point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.86,1:26:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It is just as the prophet Isaiah wrote
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.53,1:26:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at Isaiah 55:8, 9.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.04,1:26:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like to open to that, please
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.25,1:26:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—Isaiah 55:8, 9.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.13,1:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote: “‘For my thoughts\Nare not your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.30,1:26:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“and your ways are not my ways,’\Ndeclares Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.68,1:26:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For as the heavens\Nare higher than the earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.93,1:26:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘so my ways are higher than your ways
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.77,1:26:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and my thoughts than your thoughts.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.98,1:26:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine\N—Jehovah’s thoughts and language
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.27,1:27:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,must be vastly superior to those of humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.36,1:27:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When he communicates with us,\Nas he does through the pages of the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.87,1:27:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,he simplifies how he expresses his thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.70,1:27:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can understand them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.12,1:27:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then as we take in all that Jehovah says,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.83,1:27:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we can let his thinking guide our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.38,1:27:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading the Bible\Ncan be likened to peering into a mirror
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.42,1:27:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because its message\Nhas the power to allow us
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.26,1:27:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to see ourselves as we really are
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.22,1:27:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it shows us where adjustments\Nare needed
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.64,1:27:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in our attitude and conduct.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.94,1:27:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus far in this symposium,\Nwe have seen how this can actually work.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.69,1:27:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have seen two dramatizations\Nof a widowed mother
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.94,1:27:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,using the Bible to help her teenage children\Navoid being stumbled
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.03,1:27:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,by other young people\Nwho had been harassing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.91,1:27:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, her son, Gabe,\Nhad been called a coward
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.12,1:27:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,by a couple of tough-looking youths
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.37,1:27:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,while he was engaged in public witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.25,1:28:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And her daughter, Olivia,\Nhad been chided by other girls
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.38,1:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for not being interested in dating\None of the guys in her class.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.39,1:28:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Their mother used what Jehovah inspired\Nthe apostle Paul to write about
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.10,1:28:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with his ordeal in prison
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.35,1:28:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to show how he was able\Nto preserve his peace
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.10,1:28:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very difficult situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.73,1:28:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, in turn, helped Olivia and Gabe\Nto safeguard their own peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.78,1:28:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what more the mother finds\Nin the Bible to help Olivia
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.78,1:28:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid being stumbled into conduct\Nthat could rob her of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.96,1:28:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.79,1:28:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.46,1:28:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s Jake.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.71,1:28:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.38,1:28:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know she’s wild.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.92,1:28:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t even think she likes guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.59,1:28:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What if she’s into girls?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.46,1:28:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet she’s still a virgin.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.63,1:28:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia, what are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.18,1:28:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t—I don’t know how they could do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.64,1:28:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t even follow them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.40,1:29:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If this doesn’t stop,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.77,1:29:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know if I can . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.65,1:29:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re strong, OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.95,1:29:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can’t let them get to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.37,1:29:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels out of your control, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.10,1:29:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I think we need another Bible example.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.77,1:29:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when we studied\Nabout the Shulammite girl?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.78,1:29:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.15,1:29:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was pressuring her?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.49,1:29:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.21,1:30:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But she wasn’t interested in him,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.46,1:30:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just like I’m not interested\Nin that boy Jake, so . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.55,1:30:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t just him;
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.51,1:30:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there were the daughters of Jerusalem\Nin Solomon’s court.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.64,1:30:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They urged her to accept his attentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.98,1:30:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you remember what she said
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.81,1:30:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in Song of Solomon chapter 2?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.24,1:30:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “I put you under oath,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.28,1:30:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“O daughters of Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.41,1:30:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“by the gazelles and the does of the field:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.16,1:30:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not try to awaken or arouse love in me
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.04,1:30:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,until it feels inclined.”
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.63,1:30:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So despite all of the pressure,\Nwho was really in control?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.97,1:30:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She was.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.30,1:30:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No one was going to push her\Ninto something that she didn’t want to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.43,1:31:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She even said: “I am a wall.”
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.44,1:31:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the same power.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.32,1:31:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you believe that,\Nit’ll change how you handle the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.79,1:31:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now give me a hug.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.42,1:31:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys, update on yesterday’s topic.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.26,1:31:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess she still needs a man.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.10,1:31:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs something.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.81,1:31:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I just posted it. Go like my video.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.48,1:31:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All they want is to see me give in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.23,1:31:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys, update on yesterday’s topic.\NI guess she still needs . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.45,1:31:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I give them the satisfaction?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.12,1:32:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My peace comes from doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.21,1:32:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can make me stumble.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.67,1:32:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am a wall.”
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.52,1:32:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia’s mother thought\Nof another inspired Bible example,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.86,1:32:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that of the Shulammite girl\Nwho was being urged
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.78,1:32:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by the young women in Solomon’s court\Nto accept his amorous attentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.32,1:32:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite the pressure,\Nthe Shulammite girl remained in control
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.28,1:32:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for no one was going to push her\Ninto something that she did not want to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.96,1:32:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia got the point\Nas she thought to herself:
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.75,1:32:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘My peace comes from doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.25,1:32:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can make me stumble. I am a wall.’
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.09,1:33:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s obvious that the mother\Nhad a real love for God’s Word, knew it well,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.43,1:33:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and calmly and skillfully used it\Nto guide the thinking of her children
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.39,1:33:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep them from stumbling.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.56,1:33:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people these days\Nput God’s Word out of their mind
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.94,1:33:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent it from influencing their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.90,1:33:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the world’s morals decline,\Nwe must stick loyally to God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.91,1:33:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to conform our conduct\Nto his pure and holy thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.87,1:33:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and strengthen our determination\Nto live by his standards.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.71,1:33:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That is just what the apostle Paul\Nurged us to do
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.17,1:33:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 12:2.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.26,1:33:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would turn there, please\N—Romans 12:2.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.55,1:33:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote:
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.56,1:33:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“And stop being molded\Nby this system of things,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.14,1:33:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“but be transformed\Nby making your mind over,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.86,1:33:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that you may prove to yourselves\Nthe good and acceptable
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.49,1:33:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and perfect will of God.”
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.45,1:34:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Word strengthens us\Nto resist conforming
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.03,1:34:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to the corrupting practices of Satan’s world
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.37,1:34:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and to suppress temptations\Ntoward wrongdoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.92,1:34:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as we prove to ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.00,1:34:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that the will of God is good and perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.30,1:34:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then we should also accept
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.38,1:34:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that loyally obeying God\Nis the best way of living.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.84,1:34:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a direct connection\Nbetween heeding Scriptural teachings
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.30,1:34:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and obeying or enjoying genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.56,1:34:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for Jehovah’s Word\Nto have such power in our lives,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.40,1:34:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to read the Bible every day
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.44,1:34:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditate on why its counsel\Nis beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.45,1:34:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That means reading it at a pace
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.66,1:34:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows us to ponder\Non what we are reading.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.79,1:34:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And doing this helps to fix in our minds\Nthe portions
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.87,1:34:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that are especially helpful to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.75,1:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When asked why he reads the Bible\Nevery day,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.96,1:34:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,one Christian replied:
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.05,1:35:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“If I repeatedly pray to Jehovah\Nduring the day
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.97,1:35:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“and expect him to hear me,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.51,1:35:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“why shouldn’t I also listen to God\Nby reading his Word every day?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.43,1:35:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“If we want to be a good friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.48,1:35:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,why would we do all the talking?”
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.40,1:35:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes a very good point, doesn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.19,1:35:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,By reading the Bible,\Nwe are listening to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.94,1:35:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is how we get\Nhis viewpoint on matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.78,1:35:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So do you allow God\Nto speak to you every day?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.00,1:35:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We can measure\Nhow effective our Bible reading is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.71,1:35:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by the influence it has\Non our attitude and conduct.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.46,1:35:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When our peace is disturbed,\Nwe can look into the source of divine wisdom
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.72,1:35:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for God’s guidance.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.38,1:35:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking prophetically of anointed Christians
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.10,1:35:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at Isaiah 54:13, the prophet wrote:
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.39,1:35:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“All your sons will be taught by Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.89,1:35:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and [their] peace . . . will be abundant.”
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.19,1:36:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those words apply in principle\Nto Christ’s other sheep as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.32,1:36:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, when Christ’s anointed brothers,\N“the faithful and discreet slave,”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.03,1:36:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,prepare spiritual food for us,\Nsuch as this convention program,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.95,1:36:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they hold firmly to Jehovah’s Word\Nand they never water it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.96,1:36:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We always receive spiritual instruction
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.83,1:36:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that upholds Jehovah’s high moral standards,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.63,1:36:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are blessed with abundant peace
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.55,1:36:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when we accept Jehovah’s instruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.22,1:36:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah penned another prophecy\Nthat is being fulfilled today,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.60,1:36:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we find that at Isaiah 2:2-4.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.27,1:36:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw in a vision of the last days
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.27,1:36:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people from all the nations\Nstreaming to true worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.32,1:36:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And for what reason?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.32,1:36:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah wrote of Jehovah:
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.36,1:36:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will instruct us about his ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.99,1:36:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will walk in his paths.”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.87,1:36:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And in what would this result?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.87,1:36:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So that “they will beat their swords\Ninto plowshares
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.54,1:36:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“and their spears into pruning shears.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.67,1:37:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nation will not lift up sword\Nagainst nation,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.54,1:37:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,nor will they learn war anymore.”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.92,1:37:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In his goodness, Jehovah is willing\Nto teach us imperfect humans
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.51,1:37:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,how to achieve genuine,\Nabundant peace earth wide.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.97,1:37:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And he does that through the pages\Nof his own written Word.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.27,1:37:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What a privilege it is\Nto be taught by our God!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.98,1:37:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what problem may threaten\Nthe peace of our personal life,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.49,1:37:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,our family, or our congregation,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.74,1:37:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we are confident that the solution\Ncan be found in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.29,1:37:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we have learned from this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.79,1:37:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our continued love for Jehovah,\Nfor our neighbor, and for God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.75,1:37:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,will lead to our enjoying everlasting peace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.34,1:37:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in God’s new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.34,1:37:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, brothers, for teaching us
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.68,1:37:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,how love motivates our pursuit of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.39,1:38:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us now has an opportunity\Nto praise Jehovah with song.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.23,1:38:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We will sing song number 24, entitled
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.90,1:38:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come to Jehovah’s Mountain.”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.28,1:38:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s song number 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.19,0:00:24.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の統治体と
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.52,0:00:29.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界本部で働く兄弟姉妹たち\N全員を代表して
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.45,0:00:34.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを2022\N「平和をつくる」地区大会に
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.28,0:00:37.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から歓迎いたします
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:41.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcasting®の\N特別版として
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.33,0:00:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月と来月お送りする\Nこの大会のプログラムは 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.05,0:00:50.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界各地の500以上の\N言語に翻訳されました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.72,0:00:53.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目の主題は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:57.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 29:11に基づく
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.27,0:01:02.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバはその民に平和を与えて\N祝福する」というものです
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.90,0:01:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のミュージックビデオから\N分かるように
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.65,0:01:09.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはエホバの創造物を観察し
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.24,0:01:11.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言葉である聖書を読み
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.74,0:01:14.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバからの良い知らせを\N伝えることによって
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.91,0:01:17.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を味わえます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.12,0:01:20.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞビデオをお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.56,0:10:44.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の\N「平和をつくる」地区大会の
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.65,0:10:49.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の部を視聴してくださって\Nいることをうれしく思います
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.44,0:10:56.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒に86番の「エホバの教えを\N受けましょう」という歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:10:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌の番号は86番です
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.07,0:13:00.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はどのような平和を
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.82,0:13:03.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰に与えてくださるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.66,0:13:08.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした点について エホバの証人の\N統治体のスティーブン・レット兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.96,0:13:13.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の最初の話の中で\N取り上げてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:17.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話に注意深く耳を傾けましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:22.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は\N 「エホバは『平和を与える神』」です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.31,0:13:32.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを心から歓迎し
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:34.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,このようにごあいさつしたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.73,0:13:36.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「シャーローム」
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:39.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,「シャーローム」とは何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:42.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは「平和」を意味するヘブライ語で
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:46.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,この言葉は聖書の中に\N200回以上出てきます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:50.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいさつとして使う場合には\Nこういう意味になります
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.83,0:13:53.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたに平和がありますように」
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.71,0:13:57.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで この言葉を使って 皆さんを
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.13,0:14:01.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の「平和をつくる」\N地区大会に歓迎できることを
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:04.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,とてもうれしく思います
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.35,0:14:07.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会を楽しみにして\Nおられたと思いますが
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.35,0:14:10.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,その期待は決して裏切られません
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.56,0:14:14.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,3日間のプログラムを通して\Nたくさんのことを学べます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:18.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば生活のあらゆる面で\N平和を味わえるかについて
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.65,0:14:24.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の大切な教えが\Nさまざまな角度から取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.28,0:14:26.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではまず 私たち皆を
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.37,0:14:32.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会に招待してくださった方に\Nついて少し考えましょう エホバです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.08,0:14:37.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい天のお父さんについて\N考えられるのは うれしいことですね
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.80,0:14:42.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4:9で エホバは\N「平和の神」と呼ばれています
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:46.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバには愛 公正 知恵 力など
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:48.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,際立った面がたくさんありますが
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.56,0:14:51.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和も素晴らしい面の1つです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.39,0:14:54.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは平和を愛する穏やかな方です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.61,0:14:59.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使たちや忠実な人間とも\N平和な関係にあります
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.11,0:15:01.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かに平和の神だと言えます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.95,0:15:07.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エホバは私たちも平和を味わえる\Nようにしてくださるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.54,0:15:11.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 15章に答えがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:17.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 15:33を\Nご一緒に読んでみることにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.00,0:15:21.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります 「平和を与える神が
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:25.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんと共にいてくださいますように\Nアーメン」
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.39,0:15:29.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは平和を惜しみなく\N与えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.47,0:15:32.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブ 1:17にあるように
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.27,0:15:35.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,あらゆる「良い贈り物」を\N与えてくださいますが
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.48,0:15:38.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中に平和が含まれています
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.57,0:15:43.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エホバが与えてくださる平和とは\Nどういうものなのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:46.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人は平和と聞くと
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.16,0:15:49.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,争いがない状態を思い浮かべるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.41,0:15:53.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも神からの平和はそれ以上のものです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.29,0:15:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバしか与えることができない\N平和には
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.04,0:15:59.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,この上ない安心感や
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.30,0:16:02.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかで幸せな気持ちが含まれています
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.92,0:16:05.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのエホバからの平和について
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:08.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4章に書かれているので\Nそこを見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:12.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4:6, 7
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:15.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,「何も心配せず いつでも祈り
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.73,0:16:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈願を捧げ 感謝しつつ 願いを\N神に知っていただくようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.11,0:16:24.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 神からの平和が
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:29.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリスト・イエスを通して\N皆さんの心と考えを守ります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:35.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,その平和は人間の理解を\Nはるかに超えています」
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.29,0:16:40.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでエホバは 何も心配\Nしないようにと言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.67,0:16:45.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 一切心配してはならない\Nという意味でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.09,0:16:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ ここでエホバが\N私たちに注意してほしいのは
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.47,0:16:52.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配し過ぎないことです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.31,0:16:55.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,適度な心配はためになることがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.56,0:16:58.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,それによって他の人のことを気遣えたり
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.77,0:17:04.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,与えられた務めを果たせるように\N一生懸命努力できたりすることでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.20,0:17:07.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 心配し過ぎるとどうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.66,0:17:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,体や精神に悪影響があります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.04,0:17:15.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,体力や気力が奪われて\N弱ってしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.54,0:17:20.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 何も心配しない\Nつまり心配し過ぎないためには
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.21,0:17:22.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらいいのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.30,0:17:26.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4:6, 7の続きの部分に\N答えがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.84,0:17:31.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 心配しないようにと\N言ってから 何と述べているでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:34.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈り 祈願や請願をするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.89,0:17:38.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神からの平和」が得られると\N言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.65,0:17:42.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,では聖句の最後の部分は\Nどういう意味でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:49.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,「［神から］の平和は人間の理解を\Nはるかに超えています」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.28,0:17:52.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 神からの平和が\Nあまりに素晴らしいので
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:56.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間には十分に理解できない\Nということです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.46,0:18:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちには説明が\Nつかないこともあります
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.25,0:18:03.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配や不安で頭がいっぱいになって
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.42,0:18:06.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,八方ふさがりのように思える時に
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.34,0:18:10.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに「平和を与えてください」と\Nお願いするとします
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.39,0:18:12.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうなるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.43,0:18:14.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても不思議に思えるほど
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:17.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかで落ち着いた
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:20.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な状態になることがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:22.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロレインという若い姉妹は
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.36,0:18:26.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,母親をがんで亡くした時のことについて\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.78,0:18:30.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「わたしが部屋にいる時に\N母は息を引き取りました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.91,0:18:34.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐにわたしは ⋯⋯耐え［ら］れる\N強さをお与えください と
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.49,0:18:36.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.91,0:18:42.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,するとすぐに神の平和を感じました」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.92,0:18:46.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 7節にある「神からの平和が⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:51.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんの心と考えを守［る］」とは\Nどういうことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:56.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで「守る」と訳されている\Nギリシャ語は軍事用語で
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:19:01.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,兵士たちが昼も夜も見張りをしている\N様子を思い起こさせます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.61,0:19:04.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からの平和は いわば兵士のように
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.65,0:19:09.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの心と考えを\N24時間体制で守ってくれて
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.57,0:19:14.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかで平和な状態を\N保てるように助けてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.45,0:19:19.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで考えたいのは この素晴らしい\N神からの平和を与えてもらうために
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:23.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,欠かせないのはどんなことか\Nという点です
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.50,0:19:29.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えは エホバとの親しい友情を\N築いていることです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.34,0:19:32.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロが何度も経験したように
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.39,0:19:37.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からの平和は個々の状況に\N左右されるものではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:41.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの親しい関係があれば\N得られるものです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:44.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば ある時パウロとシラスは
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:47.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道をしてひどい目に遭いました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.36,0:19:50.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人とも服を剝ぎ取られ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:53.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,棒で何度も打ちたたかれた後
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:19:55.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢屋に入れられました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.87,0:19:59.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに足かせもはめられました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.12,0:20:03.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 真夜中にパウロとシラスは\N何をしましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.96,0:20:08.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈ったり 歌でエホバを\N賛美したりしました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.42,0:20:13.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の囚人は驚きながら\N祈りや歌を聞いていました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:16.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから パウロとシラスは
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.14,0:20:18.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,とてもひどい状況に置かれていたものの
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.85,0:20:22.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からの平和を味わって\Nいたことが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:26.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,この例から貴重な教訓を\N学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.15,0:20:31.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からの平和は 個々の状況に\N左右されるものではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:33.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの親しい関係があれば
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.70,0:20:38.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつでも与えてもらうことが\Nできるものなのです
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.16,0:20:43.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここまでで エホバが平和の神で\N平和を与えてくださること
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.08,0:20:46.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,また それがどんな平和かを考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.21,0:20:52.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 平和を与えてもらうために\N何が必要かをさらに考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.13,0:20:54.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが平和を与えるのは
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:57.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分との絆を強めようと努力し
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.01,0:21:01.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,導きに従いたいと思う人たちです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.31,0:21:04.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 神からの平和を頂くには
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:06.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの道徳基準に従って
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.98,0:21:10.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,清く正しい生き方をする必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:12.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中の多くの人は
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.49,0:21:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな生き方をしたとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:17.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に受け入れてもらえると思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.78,0:21:21.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が基準を下げてくれると\N思っているのです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.58,0:21:23.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは間違っています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.96,0:21:27.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,あたかも器が 自分を作った陶芸家に
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.42,0:21:30.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の使い方について指図し
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:35.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の要求を無理やり受け入れさせよう\Nとしているかのようです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.09,0:21:37.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは受け入れられませんね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:41.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間がエホバの基準に合わせるべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.14,0:21:44.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,変わるべきなのは私たちの方で
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.23,0:21:46.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに ヤコブ 3:17には\Nこのように書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.03,0:21:54.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,「天からの知恵を持つ人は
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,第一に清く 次いで平和を求め［る］」
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.70,0:22:03.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 神からの平和を\N与えていただくためには
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.83,0:22:08.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの道徳基準に従って\N清くなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.50,0:22:13.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 48:22でエホバは\Nこのように言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.38,0:22:16.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,「邪悪な者たちに平和はない」
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.51,0:22:21.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 自分の道徳基準に従って\N生きる邪悪な人たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.10,0:22:25.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから平和を与えられず\N平和を味わうことはないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.90,0:22:30.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひエホバの基準に従うように\N努力し続けましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.40,0:22:33.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろんエホバは助けてくれますが
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.49,0:22:37.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが努力することを望んでいます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.16,0:22:39.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはいわば掛け算のように
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.74,0:22:44.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの努力を祝福してくださると\N言えます どういうことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.00,0:22:49.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの努力が0だと\Nエホバは祝福できません
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.46,0:22:52.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,0×10は何ですか 0です
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.96,0:22:58.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,0×100 1000 10000だと\Nどうですか やはり0です
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.80,0:23:04.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 何も努力しないなら\Nエホバは祝福しようがないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.14,0:23:07.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガラテア 5:22によると
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.06,0:23:11.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和は「聖なる力が\N生み出すもの」の一面です
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.65,0:23:14.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 平和をつくる人になれるよう
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.15,0:23:16.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が助けてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.61,0:23:19.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 14:26では
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:22.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が「援助者」と呼ばれています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.91,0:23:25.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですが 援助者がいるからといって
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.58,0:23:31.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの側に何の努力も必要ない\Nということではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.29,0:23:33.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えで考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.38,0:23:35.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが自分の家の外壁に
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.67,0:23:39.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,一生懸命ペンキを塗っているとします
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.05,0:23:43.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこへ友達がやって来て\N塗るのを手伝ってくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:49.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもあなたは 「自分はもう家に入って\Nゆっくりしよう」と考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.06,0:23:52.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 友達はどうするでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.23,0:23:55.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペンキを塗り続けたら\Nもう援助者ではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.19,0:23:58.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの代わりに\N働いていることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.53,0:24:01.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルカ 11:13には
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.07,0:24:06.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは「求めている人に\N聖なる力を与えてくださる」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:08.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 聖なる力を求めて
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.75,0:24:12.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,その援助者に助けてもらいながら\N努力するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.09,0:24:15.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との平和な関係を楽しめます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.21,0:24:18.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 他の人とも争うことなく
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.09,0:24:21.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲の良い平和な関係を\N持つことができるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.89,0:24:28.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が生み出すものの重要な一面で\Nある平和を愛する人たちとの交友は
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.39,0:24:31.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に素晴らしいものです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.06,0:24:36.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,眠っている赤ちゃんが夜中に\N目を覚ましてしまうことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.90,0:24:39.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな音がしたので
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:41.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,その音にびっくりして
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.37,0:24:43.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,泣き出してしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.74,0:24:46.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 親が優しく抱き上げて
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.70,0:24:50.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,安心させるように声を掛けてあやすと
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.25,0:24:52.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,落ち着きを取り戻します
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.63,0:24:57.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じように\N詩編 55:16-18にある通り
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.72,0:25:00.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデはつらい状況に直面して
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.05,0:25:02.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神に向かって叫」びました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.43,0:25:04.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると エホバがその「声を聞いて」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.89,0:25:07.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「安らぎを与えて」くれました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.68,0:25:13.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもダビデのようにつらい時に\N祈りで天の父に呼び掛けるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.56,0:25:16.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは落ち着かせてくださり
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.07,0:25:19.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,安らぎを与えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.20,0:25:24.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 エホバはぜひとも\N私たちを助けたいと思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.16,0:25:26.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤ 29章を見ると
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.54,0:25:29.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが私たちの不安を取り除いて
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.62,0:25:34.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,安らぎを与えたいと思っていることが\Nよく分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.84,0:25:37.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,29:11, 12
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.80,0:25:40.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバはこう宣言する
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.09,0:25:45.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,『私は あなたたちのために自分が\N行おうとしていることをよく知っている
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.39,0:25:49.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちに災いではなく\N平和をもたらし
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.10,0:25:52.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い将来と希望を与えたいと思っている
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.40,0:25:56.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちが私を呼び\N私のもとに来て祈る時
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.73,0:25:59.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は耳を傾ける』」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.57,0:26:02.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしいですね エホバは喜んで
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.61,0:26:06.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの心配や不安を\N取り除いてくださり
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.16,0:26:10.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分にしか与えられない平和を\N与えてくださるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.87,0:26:15.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここまでで エホバが\N平和の神であることを考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.13,0:26:18.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰に平和を与えるかも考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.21,0:26:20.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との絆を強めようと努力し
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.84,0:26:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を求める人たちです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.51,0:26:25.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,では これから考えたいのは
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.72,0:26:31.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちがどのように平和をつくる人に\Nなれるかという点です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.18,0:26:35.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオの中で統治体の\Nケニス・クック兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.81,0:26:38.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくる上で\Nこの大会のプログラムが
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:43.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう役立つかということを\N説明してくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.87,0:26:46.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体を代表して
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.87,0:26:50.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「平和をつくる」地区大会を\N視聴している皆さんを
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.87,0:26:53.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から歓迎します
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.75,0:26:59.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところで 世界本部があるここ\Nニューヨーク州ブルー湖は
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.34,0:27:02.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさに心安らぐ場所です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.34,0:27:06.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,湖面が鏡のように\N景色を映すこともあります
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.35,0:27:10.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ワシやタカが飛んでくることもあります
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.72,0:27:15.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,秋になると 山々は鮮やかに紅葉します
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.06,0:27:17.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい景色です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:20.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも もっと素晴らしいのは
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.82,0:27:26.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがご自分の組織に\N与えている豊かな平和です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.20,0:27:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが平和を与えてくださるので
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.04,0:27:33.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは国 言語 人種 部族
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.91,0:27:38.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,社会的立場の壁を越えて\N一致していられます
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.09,0:27:41.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,この平和は素晴らしいものです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.26,0:27:43.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界のどこでも分断が進み
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.88,0:27:47.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々が政治 宗教
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.55,0:27:51.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,社会問題を巡って分かれているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.56,0:27:56.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも この平和は\N偶然に生じるものではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.10,0:27:58.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなでつくり上げるものです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.02,0:28:05.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に喜ばれるには一人一人が\N平和をつくらなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.24,0:28:09.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは兄弟姉妹の平和を願っています
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.95,0:28:12.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔もそうでした
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.08,0:28:16.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの祭司は\N民のために祝福を願う際
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.67,0:28:19.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言うことになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.46,0:28:21.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,その言葉を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.96,0:28:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,民数記 6:24-26です
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.59,0:28:30.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司たちは こう言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.97,0:28:35.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバがあなたを祝福して\N守ってくださいますように
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.06,0:28:37.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが笑顔をあなたに向け
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.48,0:28:39.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,恵みを与えてくださいますように
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.98,0:28:42.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがあなたに向かって顔を上げ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.57,0:28:44.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を与えてくださいますように」
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.03,0:28:48.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,27節 「彼らは\Nイスラエルの民のために
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.87,0:28:51.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の名を言わなければならない
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.16,0:28:54.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が民を祝福するためである」
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.45,0:28:57.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも神の名を大切にし
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.42,0:28:59.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,祝福されています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.13,0:29:04.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で学べる点を概観しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.55,0:29:09.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすればエホバから平和を\N与えていただけるかを学べます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.34,0:29:14.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,第一に 神との平和について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.35,0:29:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの絆があれば
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.56,0:29:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかで平和な心を持てます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.69,0:29:23.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを一番の友達にするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.73,0:29:28.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな状況でも\N平和を失うことはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.45,0:29:33.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすればエホバと\N親しくなれるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.29,0:29:36.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭だけの知識では不十分です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.12,0:29:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどんな感情を持つ方かを知って
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.46,0:29:43.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを敬うことが必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.46,0:29:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが愛するものを愛し
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.97,0:29:48.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,憎むものを憎むのです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.51,0:29:52.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で真剣に学ぶなら
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.93,0:29:56.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバともっと親しくなれるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.89,0:30:01.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,第二に 周りの人との\N平和について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.11,0:30:05.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,家庭は安らぎの場であるべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.19,0:30:08.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,言い争わないのはもちろん
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.03,0:30:14.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のことより家族を\N優先するということです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.33,0:30:18.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,後で学びますが そのために必要なのは
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.21,0:30:21.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛と敬意 みんなの協力
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.75,0:30:24.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,良いコミュニケーション
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.38,0:30:27.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒にエホバに仕えることです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.84,0:30:34.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,第三に 試練や大変な中での\N平和について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.60,0:30:40.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会では 世界各地の\N兄弟たちの経験を聞けます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.60,0:30:44.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対 病気 失業
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.86,0:30:47.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,災害に立ち向かいながら
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.40,0:30:50.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いを心から気遣い
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.36,0:30:53.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織から助けを与えられ
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.37,0:30:57.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕え続けているという経験です
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.87,0:31:01.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,命の危険や生活の不安があっても
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.37,0:31:04.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは忍耐できるよう助け
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.59,0:31:08.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の平和を与えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.88,0:31:14.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,第四に 新しい世界での\N平和について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.60,0:31:18.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国の助けによって\N人間が完全になったら
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.60,0:31:21.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況は大きく変わります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.02,0:31:26.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 72:7の 「平和が行き渡る
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.98,0:31:31.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,月がなくなる時までも」という\N言葉の通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.78,0:31:36.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 平和が永遠に続きます
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.37,0:31:42.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは将来 素晴らしい祝福を\N与えてくださるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.04,0:31:48.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年の大会のテーマは\N平和をつくるというものです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.63,0:31:54.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくるには いろいろな面で\N努力しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.26,0:31:57.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンの影響 今の悪い世界
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.97,0:32:00.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,受け継いだ不完全さのせいで
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.39,0:32:03.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和は壊れやすいものです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.06,0:32:07.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊さないために\N真剣な努力が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.65,0:32:12.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,何ができるか みんなで学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.28,0:32:17.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和の神が いつも皆さんと\N共にいてくださいますように
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.99,0:32:22.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体全員は心からそう願っています
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.41,0:32:25.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを深く愛しているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.54,0:32:30.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひこの大会をお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.59,0:32:35.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,クック兄弟 ありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.59,0:32:39.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくるのにこの大会の\Nプログラムがどのように役立つか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.81,0:32:41.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,教えていただきました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.02,0:32:46.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 平和の神が私たちのために\N準備してくださった
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.19,0:32:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会のプログラム全体を
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.73,0:32:51.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒に少し概観してみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.74,0:32:54.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,よろしければお手元のプログラムを見て
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.82,0:32:57.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,内容に注目してください
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.66,0:33:04.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目の主題は 「エホバはその民に\N平和を与えて祝福する」というものです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.33,0:33:06.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初のシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.38,0:33:10.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を愛し 隣人を愛し\N聖書を愛するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.55,0:33:15.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の平和を味わえる\Nということについて学べます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.22,0:33:18.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年の劇形式の聖書朗読では
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.30,0:33:20.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブについて取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.97,0:33:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブが「平和に役立つこと⋯⋯を\N何でも行［う］」という点で
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.60,0:33:31.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにとってどのように素晴らしい\N手本となっているか学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.36,0:33:33.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.15,0:33:38.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,「真の正しさは平和をもたら［す］」\Nという話を聞くことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.66,0:33:43.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば周りからの圧力に\N抵抗できるかが取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.71,0:33:47.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンが食べたものが\Nライオンの体の一部になるように
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.96,0:33:53.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンは私たちに圧力をかける\Nことによってむさぼり食おうとし
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.09,0:33:56.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の世の一部に\Nならせようとしています
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.38,0:34:01.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひサタンからの圧力に\N抵抗する方法を学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.43,0:34:07.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目の午後の部では まずこの大会の\N2つ目のシンポジウムがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.65,0:34:12.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神は平和をつくってくださる！」\Nという主題です
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.23,0:34:14.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ書に書かれている
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.36,0:34:18.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和についてのエホバの約束に\N力づけられるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.95,0:34:21.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 1つの話の題は
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.54,0:34:25.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,「オオカミと子羊が\N一緒に食べ［る］」というものです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.66,0:34:30.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,現在では これはなかなか\N想像しにくいことですね
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.29,0:34:32.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に食べさせようとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:37.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,おそらく子羊がオオカミのディナーに\Nなってしまうことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.43,0:34:41.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもイザヤ書の中で\Nエホバが約束している通り
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.06,0:34:44.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来 動物同士が\N平和に暮らすようになり
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.81,0:34:49.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間と動物も平和な関係になります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.19,0:34:54.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会の3つ目のシンポジウムの\Nテーマも興味深いものです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.28,0:34:58.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,「家庭の平和に欠かせないもの」\Nというものです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.45,0:35:01.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫婦や親や子供たちが
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.24,0:35:03.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな課題を乗り越えながら
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.70,0:35:09.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように家庭の平和に貢献できるかを\N学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.29,0:35:15.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の話は 「『平和の統治者』を\N心から支持する」という題です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.09,0:35:20.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話を通して 政治的な問題で\N中立を保つことの大切さを
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.68,0:35:23.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い起こすことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.18,0:35:27.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日目の最後の話の主題は何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.44,0:35:32.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,「偽物の平和に\N惑わされないでください」です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.23,0:35:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中で考えられている平和と
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.03,0:35:40.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが弟子たちに与える\N本物の平和との違いが論じられます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.49,0:35:44.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 2日目の主題は何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.12,0:35:49.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,「汚点も傷もない平和な人と\N神に認めていただ［く］」です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.92,0:35:52.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初にシンポジウムを通して
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.50,0:35:56.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道を行い続けるための\N励みを得ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.71,0:35:59.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和の良い知らせを伝えるために
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.09,0:36:03.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな努力を払えるか学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.26,0:36:05.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の話の主題は
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.60,0:36:10.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「若い皆さん 平和につながる\N進路を選んでください」です
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.90,0:36:16.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い方々に全時間奉仕を\N行うよう励ます話です
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.07,0:36:19.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さんが全時間奉仕を行うなら
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.24,0:36:21.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい人生を送ることができ
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.91,0:36:24.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して後悔はしません
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.70,0:36:27.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に動画を見ます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.50,0:36:29.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界各地の兄弟姉妹が
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.87,0:36:32.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,さまざまな問題に直面しながらも
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.67,0:36:37.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な心を持ってエホバに仕えている\N様子を見ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.67,0:36:40.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,次は イエスの新しい弟子たちが
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.38,0:36:43.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,いよいよバプテスマを受ける時です
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.30,0:36:48.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,話の中で バプテスマ希望者たちは\N次のように勧められます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.14,0:36:51.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「『平和の道』」を\N進み続けてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.69,0:36:53.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそうすべきかというと
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.73,0:36:57.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,それがまさに最高の生き方だからです
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.65,0:37:00.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,午後の部の2つのシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.53,0:37:03.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,一連のビデオを通して学び
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.12,0:37:08.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊す人と平和をつくる人の違いを\N理解することができます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.00,0:37:14.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,その二者には本当に大きな違いが\Nあることがはっきり分かるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.67,0:37:19.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,しょっぱい塩と甘い砂糖ぐらい\N全然違います
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.63,0:37:23.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に基づく今年のドラマの第1部では
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.26,0:37:28.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えて平和をつくった\N昔の人たちについて思い起こします
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.47,0:37:35.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人たちの手本を今の私たちの生活に\Nどのように当てはめられるかを考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.61,0:37:38.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,2日目の最後の話では
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.23,0:37:42.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,「『平和という絆』を守る」方法に\Nついて取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.95,0:37:48.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを守るには 国や地方の\N文化や伝統に従うことよりも
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.24,0:37:53.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則に沿って\N行動することの方が大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.21,0:37:57.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,3日目の主題は\N「希望を与える神が⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.04,0:38:01.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんをあらゆる喜びと平和で\N満たしてくださ［る］」です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.92,0:38:06.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,午前のシンポジウムでは\N全部で7つの例を考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.76,0:38:10.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,「平和の種をまいて平和を\N刈り取った人たち」の例です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.81,0:38:14.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,取り上げられるのは ヨセフと兄たち
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.06,0:38:16.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギベオンの人たち ギデオン
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.65,0:38:20.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,アビガイル メピボセテ\Nパウロとバルナバ
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.69,0:38:23.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして現代の例です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.61,0:38:25.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く公開聖書講演を
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.03,0:38:30.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひとも大勢の方々に\N聞いていただきたいと思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.41,0:38:35.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,講演の主題は\N「神と友達になるには」というものです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.79,0:38:39.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはアダムの子孫で罪深いので
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.42,0:38:42.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,生まれつき神の友達ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.63,0:38:46.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,生まれた時は神の敵のような状態です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.76,0:38:49.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人は赤ちゃんを見てこう言います
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.51,0:38:52.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,「かわいいわね 天使みたい」
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.35,0:38:55.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも正しくはこうですね
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.15,0:38:58.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,「かわいいわね 神の敵だけど」
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.32,0:39:02.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん そのかわいい赤ちゃんには\N希望があります
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.07,0:39:05.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は その赤ちゃんを含め 全ての人が
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.57,0:39:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分と和解できるように\Nしてくださったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.16,0:39:11.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆が神の友達になれます
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.66,0:39:14.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エホバとの友情関係は
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.54,0:39:18.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにとって最も大切なものです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.50,0:39:21.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマの第2部を楽しんだ後
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.09,0:39:24.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会の結びの話を\N聞くことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.93,0:39:29.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,「誰もがエホバに仕え\N平和になる時が来る！」と題する話で
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.55,0:39:33.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びに満ちた将来について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.52,0:39:37.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,「偽ることができ［ない］」神が\N約束しているものです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.69,0:39:41.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に新しいオリジナルソングを\N一緒に歌い
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.82,0:39:45.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和の源であるエホバに\N賛美の祈りを捧げて
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.82,0:39:48.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会を終えたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.37,0:39:50.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹の皆さん
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.41,0:39:54.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,3日間のプログラムがますます\N楽しみになったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.96,0:39:58.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和の神が用意してくださった\Nこの大会を
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.21,0:40:01.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひ漏らさず視聴しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.46,0:40:03.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラム全体を通して
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.84,0:40:07.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いたくさんのビデオも出てきます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.26,0:40:10.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たちの経験談やインタビュー
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.22,0:40:12.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,またドラマ仕立てのビデオなどがあって
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.02,0:40:16.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,共感したり教訓を学んだり\Nできるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.64,0:40:18.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでもビデオを見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.98,0:40:22.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で見るいろいろな\Nビデオのダイジェストを
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.32,0:40:24.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,少しお見せしたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.11,0:40:30.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな 誰だと思う？\Nオリビアです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.28,0:40:32.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日も投票よろしく\Nオリビアはジェイクとすると思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.99,0:40:35.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,しないでしょ 超真面目だもん
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.08,0:40:38.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの子たちのところに行って\N携帯壊したかった
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.25,0:40:41.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,中立？ そんなのないんだよ！\N臆病者！
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.38,0:40:43.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなもん ごみだ
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.50,0:40:49.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨークにいた頃は悲しくて\N全然平和な気持ちではありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.64,0:40:53.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんこんにちは\Nデミュアデザインのヘイリーです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.35,0:40:57.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっとねたんでるところない？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.44,0:40:59.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,2018年6月
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.52,0:41:03.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,武装した集団が\Nうちに押し掛けてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.40,0:41:07.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,警察官は子供の頃の私の憧れでした
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.57,0:41:10.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,これ どれだけコストかかるか\N分かってんのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.11,0:41:13.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,しょうがないだろ\Nこっちは聞いてなかったんだから
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.20,0:41:15.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,マスクは？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.08,0:41:17.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,会社で何人感染したか知ってる？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.00,0:41:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼロだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.13,0:41:23.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういうことはよくあります\Nもう駄目だと思った時
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.17,0:41:27.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちを元気づけるために\N必ず何かをしてくれるんです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.01,0:41:31.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な関係を取り戻せて本当に良かった
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.22,0:41:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界が大変なことになる前に
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.35,0:41:39.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 次の重要な点を考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.90,0:41:43.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で神から平和を\N与えていただくために
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.15,0:41:47.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは心を整えるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.07,0:41:50.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エズラ 7:10にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.11,0:41:54.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エズラは エホバの律法を\N調べて実践するため
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.45,0:41:59.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,また⋯⋯イスラエルで教えるため\N心を整えていた」
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.54,0:42:03.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果 11節にあるようにエズラは
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.63,0:42:08.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバのおきて⋯⋯の研究者」として\N熱心に奉仕できました
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.55,0:42:10.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エズラに倣って
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.97,0:42:13.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で学ぶために
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.76,0:42:17.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように心を整えることが\Nできるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.85,0:42:21.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても大切なのは 祈りと黙想です
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.94,0:42:25.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,その2つを行って 自分の心が
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.19,0:42:29.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバからの教育を受け入れる用意が\Nできているようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.45,0:42:31.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして心の中で
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.49,0:42:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが教えてくださることを\N当てはめる決意をするようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.04,0:42:40.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらにできるのは\N大会中に毎日流される
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.75,0:42:43.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミュージックビデオを\N注意深く見ることです
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.96,0:42:48.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,3日間の午前の部と\N午後の部の最初に流されます
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.05,0:42:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのミュージックビデオも\N入念に準備されていて
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.80,0:42:56.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが心を整えるのに\Nとても役立ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.56,0:43:00.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの美しいミュージックビデオを\N制作するために
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.39,0:43:04.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの時間や労力や\N費用がかけられました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.86,0:43:07.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひじっくり耳を傾けてください
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.86,0:43:11.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,音楽や映像によって心が整えられ
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.28,0:43:16.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後に学ぶ事柄を受け入れる\N用意ができるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち一人一人が この大会で\Nエホバが教えてくださることに
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.04,0:43:24.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,十分に注意を払うことができますように
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.88,0:43:28.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 85:8で次のように述べた
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.50,0:43:32.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編作者の謙遜な態度に\Nぜひ倣いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.97,0:43:36.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は真の神エホバが語ることを聞く
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.01,0:43:40.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は民に⋯⋯平和を語る」
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.93,0:43:45.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,注意深く聞くなら どうすれば\N平和をつくれるかが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.86,0:43:51.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 平和を与えてくださる\N平和の神エホバを賛美できます
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.74,0:43:55.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 今平和をつくることが\Nできるようになり
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.62,0:43:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来は平和を追い求めなくてよいのです
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.66,0:44:02.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバについて考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.33,0:44:05.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは平和を追い求めますか
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.08,0:44:07.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば平和を捕まえようとしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.92,0:44:12.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ エホバは平和を表すのです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.84,0:44:15.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい世界では素晴らしいことに
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.97,0:44:20.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも平和を追い求める\N必要はなくなります
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.27,0:44:24.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのように平和を表すことに\N専念できるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.98,0:44:29.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも今は ぜひ平和を追い求めることを\N決意しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.90,0:44:31.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,この素晴らしい大会が
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.99,0:44:34.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが平和をつくる上で
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.40,0:44:37.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな助けになりますように！
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.56,0:44:42.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,レット兄弟 ありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.15,0:44:45.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,心を整えるように助けられました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.44,0:44:50.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくるにはどうしたらよいかを\N学ぶ用意ができました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.95,0:44:55.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に考えることができるのは
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.08,0:44:57.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和と愛の関係です
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.41,0:45:00.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛を表すとどうなるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.92,0:45:05.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会の最初のシンポジウムから\Nご一緒に学びましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.63,0:45:09.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体の奉仕委員会の援助者\Nセス・ハイアット兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.84,0:45:12.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つ目の話をしてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.59,0:45:18.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は 「愛があれば平和になる\N神を愛する」です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.40,0:45:27.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.82,0:45:30.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛と平和の間には
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.57,0:45:34.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か関係があるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.28,0:45:38.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしあるなら 平和を得る上で
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.33,0:45:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛はどんな役割を果たしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.75,0:45:45.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が述べるところによれば
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.50,0:45:49.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛は平和を得るのに欠かせません
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.51,0:45:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは本当に大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.89,0:45:58.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで私たちは愛を示すようにします
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.39,0:46:01.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を学んで知っているように
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.27,0:46:04.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間は神に似た者として造られました
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.73,0:46:09.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが愛を示すことが\Nできるのはそのためです
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.07,0:46:12.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもご存じのように
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.15,0:46:14.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが住んでいる世界には
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.74,0:46:18.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛についてゆがんだ見方が見られます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.12,0:46:21.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに私たちは不完全です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.08,0:46:23.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで注意しないと
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.62,0:46:27.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの見方もゆがんでしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.30,0:46:31.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすればそれを避けられますか
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.09,0:46:37.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛し方をエホバに教えて\Nいただくことによってです
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.14,0:46:43.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,その点でエホバ以上の方はいません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.31,0:46:46.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書によれば 「神は愛」です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.73,0:46:50.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは創造者で 私たちのことを
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.32,0:46:53.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち以上によく知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.11,0:46:57.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 行うこと全てに\N愛があふれています
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.08,0:47:01.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方が愛について\N教えてくださるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.20,0:47:03.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにですか
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.42,0:47:06.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の言葉 聖書によって
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:10.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,またご自分の素晴らしい\N手本によってです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.88,0:47:13.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを知るにつれて
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.34,0:47:16.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の愛とは何かが分かってきます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.76,0:47:20.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 愛を行動で表す点で
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.10,0:47:22.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスに倣えます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.56,0:47:25.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちがそうするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.27,0:47:28.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の平和を味わえます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.19,0:47:31.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムで
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.40,0:47:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛があれば平和になることを学びます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.74,0:47:40.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,神への愛 隣人への愛 聖書への愛が
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.66,0:47:43.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように平和につながるかです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.87,0:47:47.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず神への愛を考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.71,0:47:50.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を味わうために
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.80,0:47:54.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛はどれほど大切ですか
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.47,0:47:58.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがマタイ 22章で\N述べた言葉から
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.43,0:48:03.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,その答えを知るヒントが\N得られるので 見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.06,0:48:09.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 22:37を読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.27,0:48:12.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず文脈を見てみると
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.57,0:48:19.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,この時イエスは律法に通じた\N男性からこう質問されました
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.58,0:48:24.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,「律法の中で最も重要な\Nおきてはどれですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.16,0:48:27.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えに注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.33,0:48:29.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,「イエスは言った
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.75,0:48:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,『「あなたは 心を尽くし\N知力を尽くし
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.55,0:48:36.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の全てを尽くして
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.26,0:48:40.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの神エホバを\N愛さなければならない」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.22,0:48:45.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが最も重要な第一のおきてです』」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.81,0:48:49.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの神エホバを\N愛さなければならない」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.44,0:48:51.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,命令です
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.44,0:48:55.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛することはとても重要で
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.82,0:48:59.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは生活の中で最も大切な関係です
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.83,0:49:02.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな人間との関係よりも
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.20,0:49:05.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなものよりも大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.16,0:49:09.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛したいと思いますが\Nどれほどですか
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.38,0:49:13.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは「心を尽くし」と言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.09,0:49:16.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.34,0:49:19.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く言葉と合わせて考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.26,0:49:22.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが使った「心」\Nという言葉はここで
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.52,0:49:26.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の気持ち 感情 欲求を指しています
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.85,0:49:31.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,神への愛に感情が\N関係するということですか
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.44,0:49:33.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.53,0:49:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも神への単なる愛情以上のものが\N関係しています
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.66,0:49:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそう言えますか\N聖句を見ましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.45,0:49:48.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはここで「自分の全てを\N尽くして」とも言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.75,0:49:51.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで持っているもの全てを使って
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.84,0:49:57.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを賛美し 神への愛を表します
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:50:00.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう1つあります
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.35,0:50:05.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,「知力を尽くし」とも\Nイエスは言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.64,0:50:09.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの思考力が関係しています
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.31,0:50:11.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは時間を取って
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.69,0:50:14.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのお考えを知るようにし
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.57,0:50:17.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに自分の考えを合わせます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.82,0:50:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと同じように考えたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.12,0:50:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどんな方で
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.16,0:50:26.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにどんなことを求めておられるか
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.21,0:50:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてエホバの目的を\N理解したいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.46,0:50:36.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような愛について考えてくると
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.09,0:50:40.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに何が含まれるかは明らかです
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.64,0:50:48.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,考え 言葉 行動 全てが含まれます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.77,0:50:51.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような愛によって
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.27,0:50:56.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは神との友情を\N持つことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.86,0:51:01.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは神との平和をもたらします
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.57,0:51:04.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,つながりが見えてきましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.74,0:51:08.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,心と知力と自分の全てを尽くして
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.67,0:51:11.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.29,0:51:14.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との平和が得られます
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.42,0:51:17.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 神との平和があれば
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.72,0:51:20.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の平和と
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.22,0:51:24.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,周りの人たちとの平和も味わえます
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.18,0:51:26.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしてですか
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.39,0:51:31.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛するとエホバに\N倣いたいと感じます
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.15,0:51:37.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが持っている性質を身に付け\N示すよう努力します
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.82,0:51:43.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 辛抱 親切 温和です
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.99,0:51:47.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした性質はほかの人を引き付け
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.96,0:51:52.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの人との平和を築くのに役立ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.96,0:52:00.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんも神と平和な関係で\Nいたいと思われるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.55,0:52:05.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも平和が奪われそうに\Nなる時もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.64,0:52:08.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ストレスを感じることもあれば
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.18,0:52:11.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひどい扱いや不公正な扱いを受けたり
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.85,0:52:16.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いことをされたりすることも\Nあるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.90,0:52:20.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな時 平和が奪われかねません
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.07,0:52:23.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで考えるべきなのは
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.78,0:52:29.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに喜ばれる仕方で\Nその状況に対処するか
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.21,0:52:36.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとも自分のやり方で何とか\Nするしかないと思ってしまうかです
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.09,0:52:40.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,では次のビデオで ある家族が
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.13,0:52:45.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの主権に対する愛と敬意を\N思い出させる聖書の記述から
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.60,0:52:49.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,力を得る様子を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.54,0:53:12.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビア！ オリビア！
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.42,0:53:15.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,早く！ 学校に遅れるわよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.84,0:53:21.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとう\N奉仕行ってくる
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.01,0:53:24.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,行ってきます じゃあね お母さん
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.72,0:53:27.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい 頑張ってね
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.77,0:53:31.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,行ってきます
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.69,0:53:40.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日も投票よろしく
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.49,0:53:42.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアはジェイクとすると思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.20,0:53:44.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,しないでしょ 超真面目だもん
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.11,0:53:46.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,真面目ぶってるだけだって\Nほんとはすごいんだから
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.58,0:53:47.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,だよね
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.70,0:53:50.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,わあ なんかすごいこっち見てる！
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.37,0:53:52.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,よし じゃあ これで上げちゃおう
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.58,0:53:55.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,オッケー できた
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.58,0:53:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.84,0:53:58.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た？\Nうん
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.25,0:53:59.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,すげえな\Nねえみんな⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.84,0:54:01.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,まじ受ける
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.22,0:54:02.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわー
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.88,0:54:04.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな ブルックだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.80,0:54:06.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,アマンダです
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.68,0:54:09.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た来た 誰だと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.39,0:54:11.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアです
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.31,0:54:12.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,で ジェイク
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.44,0:54:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日も投票よろしく
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.98,0:54:15.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアはジェイクとすると思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.27,0:54:18.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,しないでしょ 超真面目だもん
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.94,0:54:22.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,真面目ぶってるだけだって\Nほんとはすごいんだから
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.07,0:54:24.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,あ こっち見るかな？あ 見た！
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.45,0:54:26.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,超受けるんだけど なんて書く？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.57,0:54:28.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあね
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.54,0:54:31.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,男子に興味あんの？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.37,0:54:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,レズなんじゃない？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.50,0:54:33.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとだ\Nそうだね
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.83,0:54:34.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな書いてくれてる！
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.00,0:54:36.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな見たんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.00,0:54:40.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ未経験なんじゃないの？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.48,0:54:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと 見てもいい？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.56,0:54:56.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,あ もちろん
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.23,0:54:58.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.48,0:55:02.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「いつまでも幸せに暮らせます」\Nへえ どうやって？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.86,0:55:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうですよね 実は神様が⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.36,0:55:07.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや いや いや いや いや\N神じゃなくて あんただよ
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.99,0:55:09.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,あんたは何やってんの？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.41,0:55:11.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,私？ あ 人を助けようと⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.50,0:55:13.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,助ける？ そこに突っ立ってる\Nだけじゃないか
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.79,0:55:17.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,こっちは自分たちの権利のために\Nもっとやってるんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.17,0:55:18.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,あ 私は中立を⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.92,0:55:23.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,中立？ そんなのないんだよ！\N臆病者！
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.67,0:55:25.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなもん ごみだ
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.36,0:55:42.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうだった？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.32,0:55:46.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,カートの奉仕 大変だった\Nでも大丈夫
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.09,0:56:01.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな ブルックだよ\Nアマンダです
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.63,0:56:04.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た来た 誰だと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.05,0:56:05.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビア・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.84,0:56:07.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビア
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.09,0:56:10.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かあったの？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.35,0:56:17.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな ブルックだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.60,0:56:19.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,アマンダです
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.19,0:56:21.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た来た 誰だと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.98,0:56:23.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアです
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.86,0:56:25.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,で ジェイク
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.11,0:56:26.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日も投票よろしく
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.53,0:56:28.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアはジェイクとすると思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.20,0:56:30.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,しないでしょ 超真面目だもん
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.16,0:56:33.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,真面目ぶってるだけだって\Nほんとはすごいんだから
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.25,0:56:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,あ こっち見るかな？ あ 見た！
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.13,0:56:42.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,うーん 大変だったね
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.64,0:56:54.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,あのね
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.23,0:56:58.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロが経験したことを思い出したの
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.40,0:57:06.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,確か 「使徒の活動」の
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.61,0:57:08.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,16章
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.28,0:57:13.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,23節
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.21,0:57:19.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「そして 何度も打った後
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.09,0:57:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人を牢屋に入れ
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.01,0:57:28.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番に厳重に見張っておくよう命じた
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.10,0:57:33.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような命令を受けたので
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.77,0:57:36.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番は2人を奥の牢屋に入れ
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.64,0:57:38.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,足かせをはめた
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.69,0:57:42.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 真夜中ごろ
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.94,0:57:45.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロとシラスは祈ったり
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.90,0:57:48.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌で神を賛美したりしていて
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.66,0:57:51.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,囚人たちはそれを聞いていた」
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.16,0:57:56.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんで歌おうと思ったんだと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.67,0:58:00.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛していたのよね
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.75,0:58:05.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことを考えて\Nどんな気持ちになったと思う？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.22,0:58:12.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.18,0:58:15.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかな気持ちかな？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.72,0:58:17.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうね
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.77,0:58:20.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうちょっとみんなで\N続きを見てみようか
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.69,0:58:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.61,0:58:23.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.90,0:58:30.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうでしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.74,0:58:34.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,子供たち2人とも大変そうでしたね
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.83,0:58:37.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアは学校で
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.54,0:58:40.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガブリエルは伝道でです
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.67,0:58:43.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように対処すれば
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.09,0:58:49.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,この状況でエホバとの平和を保てますか
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.38,0:58:52.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な点です
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.30,0:58:54.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,大変な状況になる時
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.01,0:59:00.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち皆がこの点を\N考える必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.06,0:59:03.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはエホバの方法が\N最善であることも
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.02,0:59:09.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの統治が最善であることも\Nよく分かっています
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.99,0:59:12.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも難しい状況に置かれると
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.99,0:59:17.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 不公正な扱いや\Nひどい扱いを受けたり
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.75,0:59:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いことをされたりすると
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.63,0:59:27.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のやり方で何とかするしかない\Nと思うかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.22,0:59:35.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そうすると平和を失いかねません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.01,0:59:39.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではエホバの主権に対する敬意を
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.02,0:59:42.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように表しますか
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.98,0:59:47.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 12章にある\Nアドバイスが役立ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.15,0:59:53.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,見てみましょう\Nローマ 12章の17節からです
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.12,0:59:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,「悪いことをされても」\Nと書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.66,1:00:04.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな時にどうしたらよいと\N述べられているでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.79,1:00:09.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,「悪いことをされても 決して\N仕返しをしてはなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.55,1:00:15.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば誰の目から見ても\N良いことを行えるかを考えてください
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.93,1:00:18.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,できる限りのことをして
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.81,1:00:23.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな人とも平和な関係で\Nいるようにしましょう」
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.11,1:00:29.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 平和をつくり出す\Nということです
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.86,1:00:36.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,この言葉から エホバが無理な\N要求をされないことが分かり
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.49,1:00:39.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に感謝が深まります
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.37,1:00:42.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそう言えますか
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.33,1:00:44.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちに
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.46,1:00:48.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,できないことをするよう\N求めてはいないからです
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.34,1:00:53.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくるためにエホバが\N求めているのは何ですか
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.97,1:00:57.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,できないことではなく
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.10,1:01:00.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,「できる限りのこと」とあります
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.27,1:01:03.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの人はコントロールできませんが
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.27,1:01:07.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分自身 自分の反応は\Nコントロールできます
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.86,1:01:13.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはそれを求めておられます
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.61,1:01:18.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く19節にこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.54,1:01:21.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,「愛する皆さん 復讐してはなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.87,1:01:25.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の憤りに任せましょう」\Nなぜですか
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.71,1:01:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,「『「復讐は私がすることであり
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.34,1:01:33.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が報復する」とエホバは言う』\Nと書いてあるからです」
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.01,1:01:36.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,まとめるとこうです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.35,1:01:41.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をつくり 神の憤りに任せましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.23,1:01:45.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,復讐するかどうか\Nいつ誰に復讐するかは
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.40,1:01:48.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に決めていただくのです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.57,1:01:51.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,言うのは簡単です
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.69,1:01:55.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそうするのはいつでも簡単ですか
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.41,1:01:57.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.45,1:01:59.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデ王の手本は
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.58,1:02:02.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,この点でとても役立ちます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.08,1:02:05.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も悪くなかったのに
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.25,1:02:08.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデはサウル王に憎まれ
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.17,1:02:11.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,命を狙われるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.30,1:02:17.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてサウルは何度も\Nダビデを殺そうとします
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.89,1:02:21.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは何年も逃亡生活を送り
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.31,1:02:24.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,その間に機会が開かれても
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.94,1:02:30.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,サウルに手を出し\N殺すことはありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.94,1:02:34.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしたとしても正当化できたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.99,1:02:38.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも もしサウルを殺していたら
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.83,1:02:45.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を 特にエホバとの平和を\N失うことになったと思いませんか
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.08,1:02:51.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです では ダビデは\Nどうしましたか
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.34,1:02:54.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 部下たちに言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.34,1:03:00.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の主人に エホバが選んだ人に⋯⋯\Nこのようなことをするなど
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.18,1:03:04.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの観点からは\N考えられないことです」
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.85,1:03:08.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が分かりますか
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.77,1:03:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは自分とサウルの関係\N以上のものを見ていました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.57,1:03:18.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどうご覧になるかを考えました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.62,1:03:21.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,サウルが正されるべきなら
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.16,1:03:27.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがご自分の時にご自分の方法で\Nそうされると分かっていました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.83,1:03:30.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでダビデは辛抱し
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.75,1:03:33.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を保つことができました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.26,1:03:39.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との平和 心の平和\N周りの人たちとの平和です
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.97,1:03:42.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい手本です
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.60,1:03:47.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもエホバの主権に\N敬意を払うことにより 
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.02,1:03:52.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを待つことにより\Nエホバへの愛を表すなら
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.03,1:03:57.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を味わえると確信できます
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.36,1:04:01.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはご自分の民を祝福し
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.16,1:04:05.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を与えると\N約束してくださっています
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.87,1:04:11.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 心と知力と自分の\N全てを尽くしてエホバを愛し 
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.17,1:04:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,またエホバを待ち エホバの主権\N物事の行い方に敬意を払うことにより
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.89,1:04:22.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの愛を表していきましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.26,1:04:28.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら 神が与えてくださる\Nこの上ない平和を味わえます
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.73,1:04:32.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,人事委員会の援助者\Nラルフ･ウォールズ兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.94,1:04:36.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンポジウムの次の話を\Nしてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.40,1:04:42.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,「愛があれば平和になる\N隣人を愛する」
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.61,1:04:54.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりの時代によく見られる特徴を\N予告したテモテ第二 3章には
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.32,1:04:58.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人々は自分を愛し」と書かれています
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.03,1:05:02.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を愛するのは間違ったことですか
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.75,1:05:08.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ 自分を適度に愛するのは普通で\N必要なことでもあります
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.67,1:05:15.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスも「隣人を自分自身のように\N愛さなければならない」と言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.26,1:05:18.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは後ほどさらに考えます
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.47,1:05:24.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 最初に述べた愛は\Nゆがんだ自己中心的なものです
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.10,1:05:30.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,それによって隣人を愛するのが\N難しくなるので 平和が妨げられます
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.77,1:05:33.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある聖書学者たちによると
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.11,1:05:36.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロがテモテ第二 3:1-5で
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.36,1:05:39.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を愛することを最初に挙げたのは
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.20,1:05:41.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,後に続く悪い性質全てが
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.70,1:05:44.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこから来ているからです
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.41,1:05:48.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした性質もやはり\N平和を妨げるものとなります
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.63,1:05:52.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば テモテ第二 3:3に\Nあるように
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.59,1:05:55.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,「全く人に同意しようと」しないなら
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.26,1:06:01.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,「怒り 憤り わめき 暴言など」に\Nつながることがあります
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.06,1:06:04.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのように自制心がないと
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.39,1:06:08.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和ではなく「争いを引き起こし」ます
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.69,1:06:11.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,一方 隣人を愛するなら
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.03,1:06:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それと逆の結果
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.65,1:06:18.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の平和につながります
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.95,1:06:22.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 22章をお開きください
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.37,1:06:26.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,36節を読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.12,1:06:29.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法に通じたパリサイ派の人が
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.67,1:06:32.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスを試して言います
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.71,1:06:40.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,「先生 律法の中で\N最も重要なおきてはどれですか」
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.14,1:06:43.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,前の話で詳しく取り上げられたように
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.31,1:06:47.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは37節でこう答えます
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.39,1:06:51.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの神エホバを\N愛さなければならない」
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.65,1:06:56.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもイエスは質問に答えるだけでなく\N2つ目のおきても述べました
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.45,1:06:59.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,39節を読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.70,1:07:02.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,「第二も同様で こうです
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.12,1:07:07.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,『あなたは隣人を自分自身のように\N愛さなければならない』」
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.04,1:07:11.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスによると この2つのおきて
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.34,1:07:16.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,神への愛と隣人への愛は\Nつながっています
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.63,1:07:19.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,では「隣人」とは誰のことですか
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.55,1:07:25.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞルカ 10章をお開きください
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.73,1:07:31.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の隣人とはいったい誰でしょうか」\Nという質問に答え
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.36,1:07:37.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは 隣人として行動した\Nサマリア人の有名な例えを話します
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.86,1:07:40.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,この例えの背景として
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.57,1:07:46.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時ユダヤ人はサマリア人を\N軽蔑していました
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.33,1:07:48.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えの中で サマリア人は
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.79,1:07:53.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人の男性を助けるため\Nたくさんのことをしました
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.67,1:07:57.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人は強盗に襲われ\N半殺しにされていましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.38,1:08:02.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間のユダヤ人は知らないふりをして\N通り過ぎていきました
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.14,1:08:06.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの話を聞いた人たちは\N驚いたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.10,1:08:11.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルカ 10:33, 34には\Nこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.06,1:08:16.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ところが その道路を通っていた\Nあるサマリア人は
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.90,1:08:21.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこに来て彼を見ると\Nかわいそうに思いました
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.32,1:08:27.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで近寄り 傷に油とぶどう酒を\N注いで包帯をしてあげました
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.71,1:08:30.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから彼を自分の家畜に乗せ
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.67,1:08:35.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,宿屋に連れていって世話をしました」
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.46,1:08:40.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして36節で イエスは\N心を探る質問をします
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.80,1:08:44.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この3人のうち誰が\N強盗に襲われた人にとって
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.85,1:08:47.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人になったと思いますか」
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.10,1:08:51.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,37節の言葉は今でも当てはまります
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.40,1:08:54.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたにも 私にもです
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.90,1:08:59.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,「行って あなたも\N同じようにしなさい」
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.49,1:09:04.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 隣人とは家族や\Nクリスチャンの兄弟姉妹たちだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.87,1:09:09.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,日常接する全ての人のことです
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.46,1:09:11.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで私たちは
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.75,1:09:19.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちとは異なる人種 民族\N国籍 宗教の人も愛します
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.76,1:09:23.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,その愛をどう示せますか
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.72,1:09:28.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にローマ 13章を開きましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.73,1:09:31.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人を愛しているので
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.06,1:09:36.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を乱すようなことを\Nしないようにします
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.19,1:09:40.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはローマ 13:8-10にある
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.91,1:09:45.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からのアドバイスを真剣に\N当てはめるようにします
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.95,1:09:49.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,「誰に対しても義務を\N負わないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.46,1:09:51.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただし 愛し合うことは別です
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.00,1:09:56.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を愛する人は律法を実践しています\N『姦淫をしてはならない
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.96,1:09:59.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺人をしてはならない\N盗んではならない
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.97,1:10:04.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,貪欲になってはならない』という命令も\Nほかのどんなおきても
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.35,1:10:08.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,『隣人を自分自身のように\N愛さなければならない』という言葉に
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.73,1:10:10.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,要約されるからです
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.81,1:10:14.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛があれば 隣人に対して\N悪いことを行いません
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.40,1:10:19.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 愛があれば\N律法を実践していることになるのです」
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.03,1:10:25.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 私たちには平和な仕方で\N人に接する責任があります
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.66,1:10:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不親切に扱われても
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.04,1:10:30.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスに倣うよう努力します
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.91,1:10:34.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは侮辱されても仕返しをせず
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.13,1:10:38.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,苦しめられても相手を脅しませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.13,1:10:42.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和の統治者と平和の神に倣うとき
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.84,1:10:46.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,得られるのは心の平和です
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.43,1:10:52.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオを見て\Nひどいことをされても隣人愛を示した
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.35,1:10:57.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロの手本から学んでいる\N家族に注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.19,1:11:00.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,あんたは何やってんだよ 臆病者！\N突っ立ってるだけじゃないか
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.78,1:11:04.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,中立？ そんなのないんだよ！臆病者！\N突っ立ってるだけじゃないか 臆病者！ 
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.20,1:11:06.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,こっちは自分たちの権利のために\Nもっとやってるんだ！ 臆病者！
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.62,1:11:10.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガブリエル 今日何があったの？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.17,1:11:17.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,前にも伝道で\N怒鳴られたことはあったけど
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.30,1:11:19.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日はほんとにもう
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.71,1:11:22.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんて言うか・・・
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.22,1:11:26.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの子たちの所に行って\N携帯壊したかった
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.43,1:11:28.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,しなくてよかった
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.68,1:11:31.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん でも
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.94,1:11:34.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと後悔してる
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.73,1:11:38.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんか すっごい腹が立っちゃって
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.16,1:11:45.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫よ
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.99,1:11:48.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,続きを読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.41,1:11:52.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,26節からだったわね
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.13,1:11:59.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,「突然 大きな地震が起きて
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.34,1:12:03.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢屋が土台から揺れた
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.38,1:12:07.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,その上 全ての戸が直ちに開き
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.18,1:12:10.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆の鎖やかせが外れた
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.18,1:12:14.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番は目を覚まして牢屋の戸が\N開いているのを見ると
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.85,1:12:17.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,囚人たちが逃げてしまったものと思い
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.90,1:12:21.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,剣を抜いて自殺しようとした
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.07,1:12:23.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしパウロは大声で
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.11,1:12:27.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,『やめなさい 皆ここにいます！』と\N叫んだ
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.62,1:12:30.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番は明かりを持ってこさせてから
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.33,1:12:33.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,中に駆け込み
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.33,1:12:38.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,震えながら\Nパウロとシラスの前にひれ伏した」
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.80,1:12:44.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,地震の前 牢番が\Nパウロにした仕打ちを考えて
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.85,1:12:50.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番を憎んでも仕方がなかったよね
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.72,1:12:53.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん でもそうしなかった
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.02,1:12:56.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと 自分のことより
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.44,1:12:59.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢番の気持ちを考えたんだと思う
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.99,1:13:06.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは隣人を愛していて
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.49,1:13:09.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,命を助けようとしたんだ
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.96,1:13:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと来て
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.72,1:13:31.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,おい なんでまたここに立ってんだよ？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.56,1:13:36.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,この間言ってたこと\Nその通りだと思いました
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.15,1:13:40.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,不公正を見ながら何も\Nしないっていうのは良くありませんよね
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.23,1:13:43.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,だったら俺たちみたいに行動しろよ
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.36,1:13:48.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は 別の方法で世界が変わると考えて\N活動しているんです
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.62,1:13:50.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方法が聖書か？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.37,1:13:55.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうイメージないかもしれませんが \N1つだけ見ていただけますか
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.21,1:13:56.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つだけな
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.37,1:14:01.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はこの言葉を読んで\Nこういう活動をしようと思ったんです
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.13,1:14:05.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 24:14です
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.09,1:14:08.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「そして 王国の良い知らせは
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.60,1:14:11.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての国の人々が聞けるように
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.60,1:14:14.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中で伝えられます
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.39,1:14:17.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから終わりが来ます」
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.11,1:14:23.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオの中の場面で
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.24,1:14:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは牢番に復讐することも\Nできたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.53,1:14:31.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも ひどい仕打ちを\N受けたにもかかわらず
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.33,1:14:34.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人愛を示しました
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.25,1:14:36.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは牢番に大きな影響を与え
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.75,1:14:40.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの賛美につながりました
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.25,1:14:43.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは不完全なので
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.30,1:14:45.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人愛を育てるため
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.34,1:14:48.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,懸命に努力しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.47,1:14:53.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒ペテロに起きたことが\Nこれをよく示しています
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.18,1:14:56.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロはイエスの弟子になる前
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.31,1:15:00.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人でない人と\N交友を持ちませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.52,1:15:03.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもクリスチャンになった後
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.19,1:15:10.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,神からユダヤ人と異国人の間の壁は\N取り除かれたと教えられ
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.70,1:15:13.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを理解しました
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.29,1:15:16.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒 10:34, 35で
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.37,1:15:19.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロはこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.42,1:15:23.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神が不公平ではないことが\Nよく分かりました
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.80,1:15:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を畏れて正しいことを行う人は
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.13,1:15:31.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,どの国の人でも\N神に受け入れられるのです」
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.10,1:15:36.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロはクリスチャンになった\N異国人の家に何日かとどまり
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.94,1:15:42.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後もユダヤ人でない\Nクリスチャンたちと食事をしていました
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.07,1:15:45.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし13年後
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.78,1:15:48.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,シリアのアンティオキアにいる時
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.70,1:15:54.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロは突然 異国人の\Nクリスチャンとの交友をやめます
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.20,1:15:59.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,変化を受け入れないユダヤ人の\Nクリスチャンの反応を恐れたのです
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.42,1:16:03.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,偏見というのが根深いもので\Nあることが分かります
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.84,1:16:07.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,取り除くには努力し続け\Nなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.51,1:16:13.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人に対してエホバのような\N公平な見方を持つ必要があります
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.02,1:16:17.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのように他の人に接しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.31,1:16:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.52,1:16:24.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたたちは\Nこう命じられたのを知っています
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.69,1:16:28.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,『隣人を愛し 敵を\N憎まなければならない』
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.70,1:16:31.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし私は言います
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.24,1:16:34.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵を愛し続け
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.33,1:16:38.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,迫害する人のために祈り続けなさい」
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.37,1:16:41.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから山上の垂訓の続きの
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.33,1:16:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 5:45に記されているように
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.09,1:16:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした愛を示す理由を説明します
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.97,1:16:53.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分が天にいる父の子で\Nあることを示すためです
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.97,1:16:57.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は悪人にも善人にも太陽を昇らせ
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.85,1:17:00.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい人にも正しくない人にも
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.60,1:17:03.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,雨を降らせてくださるのです」
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.86,1:17:06.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力が生み出すこの愛は
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.03,1:17:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中で広く見られる愛と\N大きく違います
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.82,1:17:14.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,より高い原則に基づいています
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.79,1:17:20.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは 罪人でさえ良くしてくれる人\Nには良くすると言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.67,1:17:25.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 私たちは「天にいる\N父の子であることを示すため」
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.05,1:17:27.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,違っていなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.01,1:17:30.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,神とキリストが迎え入れて\Nくださったように
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.89,1:17:34.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも他の人を迎え入れます
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.39,1:17:38.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 15:7はこう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.23,1:17:41.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,「キリストが皆さんを\N迎え入れてくださったように
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.35,1:17:44.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いを迎え入れてください」
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.77,1:17:46.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここのギリシャ語が言っているのは
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.03,1:17:49.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,家や友達の輪に迎え入れるなど
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.57,1:17:54.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切にまた手厚く迎えるということです
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.87,1:17:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛が育てば偏見は枯れていくのです
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.00,1:18:04.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは皆かつて いわばよそ者で
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.25,1:18:06.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,神から遠く離れていました
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.01,1:18:13.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは「愛の綱」で\N私たちを引き寄せてくださいました
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.85,1:18:16.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリストが迎え入れてくださいました
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.89,1:18:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわばドアを開いて神の家族に\N加われるようにしてくれました
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.52,1:18:25.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが不完全な私たちを
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.48,1:18:28.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切に迎え入れてくださったのですから
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.32,1:18:33.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが誰かを退けることなど\N考えられません
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.78,1:18:37.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛する兄弟姉妹の皆さん
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.08,1:18:39.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,この邪悪な体制の終わりが近づくにつれ
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.87,1:18:44.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,分裂 偏見 敵意は増していきます
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.25,1:18:47.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバに仕える私たちは
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.09,1:18:51.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,「天からの知恵」に従い\N差別をしたりせず
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.30,1:18:53.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を求めます
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.97,1:18:56.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは喜んで
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.14,1:18:59.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの国の人々との友情を育んで
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.43,1:19:01.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,文化の違いを受け入れ
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.48,1:19:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,できるならその人たちの言語を学びます
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.40,1:19:10.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするとき 平和は\N「川の流れのように」豊かに
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.24,1:19:13.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,公正は「海の波のように」\N豊かになります
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.03,1:19:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは「全ての人に\N特に⋯⋯兄弟姉妹に
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.91,1:19:20.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,善いことを行い」ます
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.87,1:19:23.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人への愛に動かされて
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.13,1:19:25.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人のために犠牲を払い
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.34,1:19:29.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,あらゆる機会に良い知らせを伝えます
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.51,1:19:34.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの主人イエスは言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.18,1:19:37.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私があなたたちを愛した通りに
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.14,1:19:39.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちが互いを愛すること
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.64,1:19:42.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが私のおきてです」
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.81,1:19:47.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人を愛することによって\Nどんな良いことがありますか
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.44,1:19:52.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 15章でイエスが答えています
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.57,1:19:55.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,8-10節を読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.79,1:20:01.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず8節です
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.58,1:20:08.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つ目 「あなたたちが\N多くの実を結び続け
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.34,1:20:11.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の弟子であることを示すことによって
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.47,1:20:15.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の父は称賛を受けます」
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.76,1:20:19.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目 9節
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.97,1:20:24.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,「父が私を愛したように\N私はあなたたちを愛しました
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.60,1:20:28.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも私に愛されるようにしていなさい
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.07,1:20:32.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,私のおきてを守るなら\Nいつも私に愛されます
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.45,1:20:39.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が父のおきてを守っていつも父に\N愛されるようにしているのと同じです」
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.50,1:20:44.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,執筆委員会の援助者\Nロバート･シランコ兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.08,1:20:46.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムの最後の話をします
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.79,1:20:52.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は「愛があれば平和になる\N聖書を愛する」です
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.75,1:21:04.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,4000万冊もの本が並んでいるのを\N想像できますか
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.42,1:21:09.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは1300キロにおよぶ本棚を\N埋め尽くすほどの数です
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.55,1:21:13.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国ワシントンDCにある\N議会図書館の話です
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.64,1:21:17.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界最大の図書館\Nといわれるその場所には
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.47,1:21:20.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけの数の本があります
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.77,1:21:26.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中で一番読む価値がある本は\Nと聞かれたら何と答えますか
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.82,1:21:29.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロに答えてもらいましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.53,1:21:33.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは\Nテモテへの第二の手紙 3:15で
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.82,1:21:36.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖なる書物⋯⋯はあなたを賢くし
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.37,1:21:41.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリスト･イエスへの信仰による救いを\N得られるようにします」と言っています
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.75,1:21:48.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロが言っていたのは\N神ご自身の言葉 聖書のことでした
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.21,1:21:52.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は救いを得るのに必要な\N知恵を与えてくれるので
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.72,1:21:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で一番価値のある本です
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.51,1:22:01.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,本というものにそれほどの\N力があるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.94,1:22:04.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,本とその著者との関係について
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.60,1:22:08.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギルバート・ハイエットという\N作家がこう述べています
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.15,1:22:11.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,「本というのは命のない紙の束ではなく
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.78,1:22:14.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,本棚に並ぶ生きた知性である
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.62,1:22:17.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれが声を発している⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.08,1:22:19.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで1冊手に取って開くと
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.37,1:22:23.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,著者の声が時間と空間を\N超えて聞こえてくる
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.46,1:22:26.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 著者の考えや気持ちが
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.13,1:22:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの考えや気持ちに影響を与える」
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.84,1:22:35.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,本棚からこの本 聖書を\N取り出して開くと
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.72,1:22:40.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,その著者であるエホバの声が\N聞こえてきます
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.35,1:22:44.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの考えや気持ちも\N伝わってきますか
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.65,1:22:46.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りです
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.73,1:22:50.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは エレミヤ 29:11で\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.99,1:22:52.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は あなたたちのために
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.03,1:22:56.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が行おうとしていることを\Nよく知っている⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.49,1:23:00.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い将来と希望を\N与えたいと思っている」
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.20,1:23:03.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 27:11ではこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.67,1:23:06.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「賢くあって 私の心を喜ばせよ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.71,1:23:10.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,私をあざける者に\N私が答えるためである」
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.09,1:23:16.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが聖書という貴重な本を\N与えてくださったことに感謝できます
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.39,1:23:19.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,それによって エホバの\N考えや気持ちを知り
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.47,1:23:24.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに近づき 永遠の命を\N得る方法を学べます
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.35,1:23:27.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはエホバを愛しているので
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.77,1:23:33.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を通してエホバが言われることも\N愛し大切にします
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.40,1:23:35.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 119編の作者は
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.03,1:23:38.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさにそのように感じていました
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.70,1:23:45.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞ聖書の詩編 119編を開いて\N161節をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.33,1:23:51.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 119:161の\N後半にこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.92,1:23:57.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,「しかし私の心が畏れるのは\Nあなたの言葉」
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.39,1:24:03.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに167節と168節も\N読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.48,1:24:07.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの教えを守り こよなく愛する
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.15,1:24:10.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの命令と教えを守る
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.44,1:24:14.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私がすることをあなたは\N全て知っている」
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.11,1:24:18.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖書筆者は 神の命令と教えを
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.66,1:24:23.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,単に冷たい法律を並べたもの\Nとは見ませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.91,1:24:28.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを重荷とも考えなかったに\N違いありません
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.54,1:24:33.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが最高の生き方をする\N土台となるということを知っていました
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.97,1:24:37.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 神の命令と教えを\N学ぶだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.80,1:24:42.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを守りたいという願いも\N持っていました
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.68,1:24:47.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,この詩編から分かるように\N神の言葉こそ学ぶ価値があり
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.77,1:24:50.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の命令と教えを知っていれば
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.40,1:24:53.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,それ以外の全てのことを\N知っている人より
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.53,1:24:57.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,はるかに賢くなることができます
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.11,1:25:01.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,165節にも注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.29,1:25:03.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,165節
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.00,1:25:07.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,「豊かな平和はあなたの律法を\N愛する人たちのもの
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.88,1:25:11.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人たちはどんなものにも\Nつまずかない」
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.96,1:25:16.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが聖書を愛する大きな理由です
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.43,1:25:20.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに従えば平和になるということです
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.35,1:25:22.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰もが平和を願っていますが
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.72,1:25:24.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすればそれを得られるか
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.89,1:25:27.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書から分かります
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.48,1:25:30.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 聖書に従うことを選び
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.36,1:25:33.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,試練に直面するとしてもそうします
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.32,1:25:38.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,試練によって心の平和が\N奪われそうになる時もです
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.24,1:25:42.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 私たちが毎日の生活で\N経験することをご存じで
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.99,1:25:45.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.00,1:25:49.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言葉を愛してそれに従うなら
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.13,1:25:52.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の言動や生活で生じる\N他の事柄によって
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.92,1:25:57.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまずくこと 信仰を\N妨げられることはありません
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.72,1:26:03.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書への愛があれば どのように\N平和になり それを保てますか
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.31,1:26:08.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖書全体は神の聖なる力の\N導きによって書かれた」ので
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.98,1:26:11.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな場面でも役に立ちます
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.48,1:26:16.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は私たちよりはるかに知恵のある方で
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.24,1:26:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むと 物事を神の高い観点で\N見ることができます
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.03,1:26:25.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者イザヤが\Nイザヤ 55:8, 9で
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.97,1:26:28.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,書いた通りです どうぞ
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.10,1:26:32.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 55:8, 9を\Nお開きください
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.00,1:26:35.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.13,1:26:40.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の考えはあなたたちの考えとは違い
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.18,1:26:44.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちの行いは私の行いとは違う
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.64,1:26:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,天が地より高いように 私の行いは\Nあなたたちの行いより高く 
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.48,1:26:53.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の考えはあなたたちの考えより高い」
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.90,1:26:57.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうですか エホバの考えや言葉は
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.36,1:27:00.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間よりはるかに優れているのです
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.07,1:27:04.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは聖書を通して人間と\Nコミュニケーションを取る時
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.99,1:27:10.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間が理解できるようにご自分の\N考えを分かりやすく表現されます
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.08,1:27:13.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言うことを取り入れていくと
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.75,1:27:18.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の考えをエホバの考えに\N合わせられます
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.22,1:27:22.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むのは鏡を見るようなものです
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.30,1:27:28.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の言葉によって 自分が\N本当にどんな人かを見ることができ
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.14,1:27:33.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の態度や行いのどこを調整\Nしたらいいかが分かるからです
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.73,1:27:38.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,これがどう役立つかを\Nこのシンポジウムで見てきました
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.70,1:27:43.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つのビデオで やもめの母親は\N自分の10代の子供たちが
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.58,1:27:46.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの若者から圧力を\N受けても屈しないよう
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.79,1:27:49.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を使って助けていました
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.87,1:27:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子のガブリエルは\N公共エリア伝道の時に
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.17,1:27:58.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,いかつい若者たちから\N臆病者と言われていました
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.22,1:28:02.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,娘のオリビアは クラスの男子と\Nデートをする気がないことで
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.80,1:28:06.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの女子からいじめられていました
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.52,1:28:10.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても難しい状況でどのように\N平和を保てるかについて
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.02,1:28:14.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,母親は 聖なる力の\N導きによって書かれた
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.02,1:28:19.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロの投獄に関する\N記述を使って教えていました
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.70,1:28:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはオリビアとガブリエルにとって
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.32,1:28:25.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても役立つ内容でした
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.66,1:28:29.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,では娘が平和を失うような\N行いを避けるよう 
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.33,1:28:35.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,母親が聖書の別の記述を使って\Nどのように助けるか見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.13,1:28:38.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た来た 誰だと思う？ オリビアです
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.51,1:28:40.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,で ジェイク\Nオリビアはジェイクとすると思う？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.80,1:28:43.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとはすごいんだから\N男子に興味あんの？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.47,1:28:47.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,レズなんじゃない？\Nまだ未経験なんじゃないの？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.68,1:28:50.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビア 大丈夫？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.31,1:28:55.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんで なんでこんなことするのか\N分かんない
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.73,1:28:58.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,別に仲良くもないのに
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.40,1:29:01.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,また同じことされたら
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.03,1:29:05.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらいいか・・・
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.75,1:29:12.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと大丈夫\N頑張れる強さを持ってるじゃない
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.09,1:29:21.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分ではどうにも\Nできないように思うよね
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.19,1:29:37.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえ 聖書の別の話を\N思い出したんだけど
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.82,1:29:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,シュラムの乙女について勉強したの\N覚えてる？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.91,1:29:46.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん 覚えてる
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.24,1:29:49.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰がアプローチしてきた？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.54,1:29:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモン
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.17,1:30:03.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも彼女にその気はなかった
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.59,1:30:06.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私がジェイクに興味がないのと同じで
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.72,1:30:09.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもソロモンだけじゃなかったわね
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.98,1:30:13.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモンの宮廷にいた女性たちも
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.73,1:30:19.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモンの申し出を\N受け入れるよう言ってきた
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.99,1:30:23.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもなんて答えたんだっけ？
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.99,1:30:26.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ソロモンの歌」2章
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.54,1:30:32.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エルサレムの女性たち
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.12,1:30:37.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんはガゼルや野の雌鹿の\N美しさが分かる女性
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.17,1:30:42.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,誓ってください\N私の愛を無理に呼び起こさないと」
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.22,1:30:48.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろんな圧力があって\N彼女は圧力に負けちゃったかしら？
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.97,1:30:52.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,負けなかった
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.23,1:30:55.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰に何を言われても
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.27,1:30:57.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,言いなりにはならなかった
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.53,1:31:04.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は城壁」とも言っているわね
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.37,1:31:10.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたも同じように強くなれるわよ
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.71,1:31:16.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう思っていれば\N気持ちを強く持って行動できるわね
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.09,1:31:21.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたならできる
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.52,1:31:34.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな きのうの続き
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.94,1:31:37.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアはまだジェイクと\Nやってないみたい
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.23,1:31:40.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビア彼氏募集中
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.28,1:31:47.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,動画アップしたよ いいね押してね
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.58,1:31:50.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちと同じことを\Nさせようとしてるだけなんだ
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.91,1:31:52.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえみんな きのうの続き
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.00,1:31:55.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアはまだジェイクと\Nやってないみたい
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.50,1:31:59.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあの子たちの言いなりにはならない
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.25,1:32:03.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しいことをしていれば\N平和な気持ちでいられる
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.63,1:32:06.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は屈しない
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.31,1:32:13.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は城壁」
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.53,1:32:30.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,母親はシュラムの乙女の\N手本を思い出しました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.16,1:32:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,その乙女はソロモンの\N申し出を受け入れるよう
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.54,1:32:37.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,宮廷の女性たちから圧力を受けました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.33,1:32:41.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもシュラムの乙女はほかの人の\N言いなりになったりせず
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.21,1:32:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,したくないことをさせようとする\N圧力に負けませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.97,1:32:49.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,オリビアは要点を理解して言いました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.30,1:32:52.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「正しいことをしていれば\N平和な気持ちでいられる
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.64,1:32:56.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は屈しない 私は城壁」
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.98,1:33:00.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,明らかに母親は聖書を本当に愛し
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.15,1:33:05.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく知っていて 圧力に屈しないよう\N子供たちの考えを導くために
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.53,1:33:09.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を穏やかに上手に使っていました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.53,1:33:16.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では多くの人が聖書のことなど\Nお構いなしで見向きもしません
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.71,1:33:21.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも モラルが低下しても\N私たちは聖書にしっかり従って
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.55,1:33:24.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の聖なる考えに沿って行動し
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.80,1:33:29.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の基準に従う決意を\N強めなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.51,1:33:35.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはまさにローマ 12:2で\N使徒パウロが勧めている点です
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.89,1:33:42.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にローマ 12:2の\N言葉を読みましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.15,1:33:44.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.19,1:33:48.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,「そして 今の体制によって\N形作られるのをやめてください
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.32,1:33:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,かえって 考え方を新しくする\Nことによって自分を変化させましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.16,1:33:59.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 神の善い意志 喜ばしい\N完全な意志を見極めるためです」
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.46,1:34:03.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書から力を得て 世に抵抗し
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.09,1:34:05.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,堕落した習慣を退け
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.38,1:34:09.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を制して悪い行いを\Nしないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.97,1:34:12.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは神の善い意志
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.93,1:34:15.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,完全な意志を見極めると 
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.39,1:34:20.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,神にしっかり従うのが最善の生き方で\Nあることも認めるようになります
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.81,1:34:24.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の教えを生活の中で\N当てはめることは
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.36,1:34:29.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず真の平和という結果につながります
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.37,1:34:33.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバの言葉が\N生活に影響を及ぼすには 
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.12,1:34:35.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を毎日読んで 
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.16,1:34:40.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのアドバイスがなぜためになるかを\Nじっくり考える必要があります
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.46,1:34:43.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでいる内容を\Nじっくり考えられるペースで
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.75,1:34:46.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,読まなければならないということです
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.84,1:34:49.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な点を記憶にとどめるのに
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.84,1:34:52.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは役立ちます
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.68,1:34:58.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある兄弟は 聖書を毎日読む理由を\N尋ねられてこう答えました
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.69,1:35:00.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「日中 何度もエホバに祈り
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.86,1:35:03.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを聞いてくださるよう\N期待するのであれば
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.73,1:35:05.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分も毎日聖書を読んで
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.94,1:35:09.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉に耳を傾けるべきだと思います
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.16,1:35:14.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い友でいたければ こちらばかりが\N話すことはないはずです」
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.45,1:35:17.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かにその通りですね
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.16,1:35:20.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むなら\Nエホバの声を聞くことができ
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.58,1:35:24.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようにしてエホバの見方を\N学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.67,1:35:30.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 毎日神に話して\Nいただくようにしていますか
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.76,1:35:32.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書通読の効果性は
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.89,1:35:37.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の態度や行いに与える\N影響で測れます
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.43,1:35:41.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が乱される時\N神の知恵と導きを求めて
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.65,1:35:44.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を調べましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.19,1:35:46.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,天に行くクリスチャンについて
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.24,1:35:50.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 54:13は\Nこう預言しています
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.36,1:35:53.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの子たちは皆エホバに教えられ
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.87,1:35:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,豊かな平和を味わう」
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.87,1:36:01.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,この描写は キリストの\Nほかの羊にも当てはまります
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.33,1:36:06.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,感謝すべきことに キリストの兄弟\Nである「忠実で思慮深い奴隷」は
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.26,1:36:09.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会を含め 私たちを教える時 
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.55,1:36:14.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書にしっかり従い その教えを\N曖昧にしたりはしません
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.06,1:36:16.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが受ける教えはいつも
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.85,1:36:20.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの高い道徳基準に沿ったもので
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.60,1:36:23.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの教えを受け入れる時 
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.31,1:36:27.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,豊かな平和を味わうことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.07,1:36:31.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤが書いた別の預言も\N今日実現しています
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.03,1:36:34.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 2:2-4です
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.91,1:36:37.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりの時代の幻の中で
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.08,1:36:40.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての国の人々がエホバを崇拝します
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.33,1:36:43.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか\Nイザヤはこう書いています
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.92,1:36:46.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神はご自分の道について\N教えてくださる
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.01,1:36:49.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはその道を歩もう」
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.97,1:36:53.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな結果になりますか\Nこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.05,1:36:57.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「彼らは剣をすきに\Nやりを鎌に作り替える
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.68,1:37:00.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,国は国に向かって剣を振り上げず
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.85,1:37:04.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らはもはや戦いを学ばない」
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.90,1:37:08.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,善い神であるエホバは\N不完全である私たちに
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.28,1:37:13.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中で本当の平和を実現する\N方法を教えてくださっています
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.99,1:37:17.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の言葉である聖書を通してです
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.16,1:37:21.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に教えられるのは\N本当に素晴らしいことです
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.92,1:37:24.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かの問題が起きて
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.04,1:37:29.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,個人 家族 会衆の平和が\N脅かされるとしても
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.67,1:37:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に解決策があると確信できます
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.26,1:37:36.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムで学んだように
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.68,1:37:41.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと隣人と聖書への\N愛を持ち続けるなら
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.73,1:37:43.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の新しい世界で
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.77,1:37:48.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠に平和を味わうことが\Nできるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.26,1:37:51.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たち ありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.89,1:37:56.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛があれば平和を\Nつくれることが分かりました
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.35,1:37:58.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではここで歌を歌って
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.44,1:38:01.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを賛美することにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.15,1:38:07.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,24番の「エホバの山に登ろう」\Nという歌をご一緒に歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.40,1:38:10.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,24番です
